10
00:01:27.946 --> 00:01:30.563
<i>A trillion tons of dirt and rock</i>

11
00:01:30.596 --> 00:01:32.700
<i>hurtled into the atmosphere,</i>

12
00:01:32.701 --> 00:01:35.494
<i>creating a suffocating blanket of dust</i>

13
00:01:35.495 --> 00:01:38.205
<i>the sun was powerless to penetrate</i>

14
00:01:38.206 --> 00:01:40.222
<i>for a thousand years.</i>

15
00:01:40.777 --> 00:01:42.034
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYS)

16
00:01:48.717 --> 00:01:50.073
<i>It happened before.</i>

17
00:01:52.003 --> 00:01:53.847
<i>It will happen again.</i>

18
00:01:55.598 --> 00:01:58.378
<i>It's just a question of when.</i>

19
00:02:08.424 --> 00:02:09.550
(GLASS BREAKING)

20
00:02:10.104 --> 00:02:11.237
(EXPLOSIONS)

21
00:02:14.284 --> 00:02:15.595
(INDISTINCT
CHATTER ON PA)

22
00:02:19.288 --> 00:02:20.886
MAN: (ON RADIO)
<i>Houston, affirmative.</i>

23
00:02:23.043 --> 00:02:24.501
<i>Now try again.</i>

24
00:02:24.502 --> 00:02:25.788
(MAN CHATTERING
ON RADIO)

25
00:02:28.089 --> 00:02:29.440
Almost got it.

26
00:02:29.799 --> 00:02:30.799
(GRUNTS)

27
00:02:32.927 --> 00:02:34.178
<i>Atlantis, I'm almost there.</i>

28
00:02:34.210 --> 00:02:36.722
Houston, Pete's
lookin' real strong.

29
00:02:36.723 --> 00:02:37.724
Okay, Pete.

30
00:02:37.756 --> 00:02:39.621
We got that coupling
on the board here now.

31
00:02:40.059 --> 00:02:41.715
We'll give you the
go-ahead from down here

32
00:02:41.748 --> 00:02:42.777
<i>when it's in alignment.</i>

33
00:02:43.480 --> 00:02:44.480
MAN: <i>Sounds good.</i>

34
00:02:45.023 --> 00:02:46.300
<i>Give me ten seconds.</i>

35
00:02:47.260 --> 00:02:48.261
(SIGHS)

36
00:02:48.654 --> 00:02:50.012
His heart rate's racing.

37
00:02:50.380 --> 00:02:51.730
Hey, Pete.
It's Truman.

38
00:02:51.763 --> 00:02:52.622
MAN: <i>Hey.</i>

39
00:02:52.655 --> 00:02:54.202
How you doing up there, hoss?

40
00:02:54.234 --> 00:02:54.865
<i>Pretty good.</i>

41
00:02:54.866 --> 00:02:57.084
Listen, Pete, we got an eye
on your meds here.

42
00:02:57.327 --> 00:02:58.660
<i>I'll give you a buffalo nickel</i>

43
00:02:58.661 --> 00:03:00.662
if you'll calm down just a little bit.

44
00:03:00.663 --> 00:03:01.764
<i>Can you do that for me?</i>

45
00:03:01.834 --> 00:03:02.998
Whatever you say.

46
00:03:03.458 --> 00:03:05.585
TRUMAN: <i>Okay, now,
we got plenty of time.</i>

47
00:03:05.617 --> 00:03:06.748
Buddy, so don't you worry.

48
00:03:08.933 --> 00:03:10.311
- (INDISTINCT CHATTER)
- <i>Okay.</i>

49
00:03:11.200 --> 00:03:12.381
<i>Looking good here.</i>

50
00:03:13.491 --> 00:03:14.468
He'll be all right.

51
00:03:14.469 --> 00:03:15.386
<i>Go ahead, Atlantis.</i>

52
00:03:15.418 --> 00:03:16.595
<i>Uh, roger that, Houston.</i>

53
00:03:16.596 --> 00:03:18.334
Suggest we start reeling Pete in.

54
00:03:19.451 --> 00:03:20.616
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

55
