We've lost all contact!

67
00:03:52.594 --> 00:03:54.336
Stuart, play that tape back!

68
00:03:58.388 --> 00:03:59.389
<i>Whoa!</i>

69
00:04:00.040 --> 00:04:01.243
(SCREAMING) <i>Houston!</i>

70
00:04:04.018 --> 00:04:05.727
Multiple bogies!
Multiple bogies!

71
00:04:05.728 --> 00:04:07.146
Sector five, niner.

72
00:04:07.178 --> 00:04:08.897
I have three. Now five.

73
00:04:08.898 --> 00:04:11.024
- Unidentified tracks.
- My screen's full.

74
00:04:11.025 --> 00:04:13.152
Multiple tracks headed toward
the Atlantic seaboard!

75
00:04:13.153 --> 00:04:14.820
This could be a surprise missile attack.

76
00:04:14.821 --> 00:04:16.063
(ALARM BLARING)

77
00:04:20.577 --> 00:04:22.077
Mr. President,
the shuttle Atlantis

78
00:04:22.109 --> 00:04:23.670
just exploded in space.

79
00:04:23.913 --> 00:04:25.452
Okay, I want three groups!

80
00:04:26.014 --> 00:04:28.041
One, internal malfunction.

81
00:04:28.042 --> 00:04:29.870
Get the log tape.
Start working back.

82
00:04:29.902 --> 00:04:30.961
Maybe it's a glitch.

83
00:04:30.962 --> 00:04:32.126
Two, I want NORAD,

84
00:04:32.159 --> 00:04:33.755
Space Command
and the 50th tactical,

85
00:04:33.756 --> 00:04:35.075
comparing all the space junk

86
00:04:35.107 --> 00:04:36.425
you tracked in every orbit.

87
00:04:36.426 --> 00:04:37.287
I want you to check,

88
00:04:37.319 --> 00:04:38.969
recheck
and then do it all over again.

89
00:04:38.970 --> 00:04:40.952
Number three, wild cards.

90
00:04:40.985 --> 00:04:41.972
Anything and everything.

91
00:04:41.973 --> 00:04:44.348
All right? Now, Big Ross,
get on the telephone.

92
00:04:44.380 --> 00:04:45.559
Wake up 11,000 people.

93
00:04:45.560 --> 00:04:47.102
- Walt, get 'em going.
- Let's go!

94
00:04:47.103 --> 00:04:48.105
DOTTIE: <i>Karl!</i>

95
00:04:48.715 --> 00:04:49.722
<i>Karl!</i>

96
00:04:51.082 --> 00:04:51.988
<i>Karl!</i>

97
00:04:53.985 --> 00:04:55.063
Karl!

98
00:04:55.524 --> 00:04:56.945
Your Stouffer's pot pie's

99
00:04:56.946 --> 00:04:59.615
been on the table
almost ten hours.

100
00:04:59.616 --> 00:05:01.992
- I want a divorce.
- Dottie, I'm on to something big here.

101
00:05:01.993 --> 00:05:03.336
I... I don't know what this is,

102
00:05:03.368 --> 00:05:05.412
but it looks like
something's burnin' up there.

103
00:05:05.413 --> 00:05:06.610
Go get my phone book, will you?

104
00:05:06.642 --> 00:05:07.331
Get my phone book.

105
00:05:07.332 --> 00:05:09.333
Get those names
of those guys from NASA.

106
00:05:09.334 --> 00:05:10.518
Excuse me!

107
00:05:10.550 --> 00:05:14.134
Am I wearing a sign
that says, "Karl's Slave"?

108
00:05:14.380 --> 00:05:17.633
Go get my goddamn phone book!

109
00:05:17.634 --> 00:05:18.743
Get the book!

110
00:05:18.939 --> 00:05:19.947
Get the book!

111
00:05:20.072 --> 00:05:21.165
Get the book!

112
00:05:25.475 --> 00:05:26.975
Space Command
is reporting negative.

113
00:05:27.008 --> 00:05:28.685
That is zero global launches.

114
00:05:29.145 --> 00:05:30.509
It might just be a
piece of the shuttle

115
00:05:30.541 --> 00:05:31.480
breaking up as it comes in.

116
00:05:31.481 --> 00:05:32.773
It might be Santa Claus.

117
00:05:32.774 --> 00:05:36.109
Until we get definitive,
reliable confirmation, General,

118
00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:37.422
<i>we go to DEFCON Three.</i>

119
00:05:38.938 --> 00:05:40.196
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

120
