You might wanna listen to him.

509
00:19:42.664 --> 00:19:44.791
General, if you consider your target,

510
00:19:44.792 --> 00:19:47.543
her composition, her dimensions,

511
00:19:47.544 --> 00:19:49.462
her sheer velocity,

512
00:19:49.463 --> 00:19:51.172
you could fire every nuke
you've got on her,

513
00:19:51.173 --> 00:19:52.969
she'll just smile at you
and keep on coming.

514
00:19:54.259 --> 00:19:56.844
You should know that
the president's scientific advisors

515
00:19:56.845 --> 00:19:59.258
are suggesting that a
nuclear blast could change...

516
00:19:59.286 --> 00:20:00.613
...this asteroid's trajectory.

517
00:20:01.456 --> 00:20:03.487
I know the president's
chief scientific advisor.

518
00:20:03.516 --> 00:20:04.729
We were at M.I.T. together.

519
00:20:05.296 --> 00:20:06.933
And, in a situation like this...

520
00:20:07.314 --> 00:20:08.898
(CLEARS THROAT) You really
don't wanna take the advice

521
00:20:08.899 --> 00:20:10.612
from a man who got
a C-minus in astrophysics.

522
00:20:12.694 --> 00:20:14.537
The president's advisors are...

523
00:20:14.891 --> 00:20:15.896
...wrong.

524
00:20:16.522 --> 00:20:17.537
I'm right.

525
00:20:17.866 --> 00:20:20.284
Hitting the rock from
the outside won't do the job.

526
00:20:20.285 --> 00:20:21.686
Imagine a firecracker...

527
00:20:22.248 --> 00:20:23.496
...in the palm of your hand.

528
00:20:23.497 --> 00:20:24.989
You set it off. What happens?

529
00:20:26.043 --> 00:20:27.293
Burn your hand, right?

530
00:20:27.543 --> 00:20:29.957
You close your fist around
the same firecracker...

531
00:20:29.986 --> 00:20:31.337
...and set it off...

532
00:20:31.338 --> 00:20:32.355
(SCOFFS)

533
00:20:33.268 --> 00:20:35.588
Your wife's gonna be opening your
ketchup bottles the rest of your life.

534
00:20:36.041 --> 00:20:38.219
Are you suggesting that we blow
this thing up from the inside?

535
00:20:38.220 --> 00:20:40.429
- That's exactly what I'm saying.
- How?

536
00:20:40.461 --> 00:20:41.976
(SIGHS) We drill.

537
00:20:42.969 --> 00:20:44.773
We bring in the world's best
deep-core driller.

538
00:20:45.060 --> 00:20:47.645
Harry, get up here.
We're takin' a hit.

539
00:20:47.646 --> 00:20:49.480
- Get A.J. up here!
- Come on!

540
00:20:49.481 --> 00:20:50.565
Oh, shit!

541
00:20:50.566 --> 00:20:51.583
(SCREAMING)

542
00:20:51.775 --> 00:20:53.372
Send another pipe down! Right now!

543
00:20:54.069 --> 00:20:55.444
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

544
00:20:55.445 --> 00:20:56.779
It's a gas pocket!

545
00:20:56.780 --> 00:20:59.490
I told you! Am I lucky,
or am I just a genius?

546
00:20:59.491 --> 00:21:01.494
I shut it down for a reason,
you jackass!

547
00:21:01.522 --> 00:21:02.618
The relief valve's...

548
00:21:02.837 --> 00:21:03.838
(SCREAMING)

549
00:21:05.489 --> 00:21:07.192
Shut off the number two valve!

550
00:21:07.294 --> 00:21:09.551
Grace! Get the
clients out of here now!

551
00:21:09.960 --> 00:21:11.241
(ALARM SOUNDING)

552
00:21:12.381 --> 00:21:13.475
No, Daddy!

553
00:21:14.655 --> 00:21:15.656
(SCREAMING)

554
00:21:16.292 --> 00:21:18.663
Chick, get 'em outta here!
Get 'em off the rig now!

555
00:21:19.862 --> 00:21:20.870
(ROARING)

556
00:21:24.432 --> 00:21:25.815
Get the hell down!

557
00:21:26.332 --> 00:21:27.722
This thing is gonna blow!

558
00:21:31.148 --> 00:21:32.148
(SCREAMING)

559
00:21:33.358 --> 00:21:34.623
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

560
00:21:35.628 --> 00:21:37.060
Chick, get down now!

561
00:21:38.405 --> 00:21:39.928
Get down!

562
00:21:41.681 --> 00:21:42.992
DAN: <i>Three dozen research calls,</i>

563
00:21:42.993 --> 00:21:44.952
<i>and every time,
the same man is recommended.</i>

564
00:21:44.953 --> 00:21:47.288
<i>He's worked on every terrain
this planet can offer.</i>

565
00:21:47.289 --> 00:21:49.540
<i>Whenever they said it couldn't be
drilled, this guy drilled it.</i>

566
00:21:49.541 --> 00:21:50.916
(SHOUTS) Everybody all right?

567
00:21:51.140 --> 00:21:53.033
We struck oil, baby!

568
00:21:53.462 --> 00:21:55.630
Somebody could've got killed
out here today.

569
00:21:55.631 --> 00:21:57.746
You want that on your conscience?

570
00:21:59.593 --> 00:22:01.552
High thumb. You are man, Harry.

571
00:22:01.553 --> 00:22:03.012
Thumbs high.

572
00:22:03.013 --> 00:22:04.102
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

573
00:22:06.975 --> 00:22:08.060
You're fired.

574
00:22:13.482 --> 00:22:15.083
Who's Harry Stamper?

575
00:22:16.085 --> 00:22:17.488
Hey, I'm Harry Stamper.

576
00:22:17.632 --> 00:22:18.819
What's all this about?

577
00:22:18.820 --> 00:22:20.641
Mr. Stamper, I'm
General Montgomery...

578
00:22:20.669 --> 00:22:22.490
...commander of the Pacific Air Forces.

579
00:22:22.491 --> 00:22:24.617
I've been sent here
by the Secretary of Defense

580
00:22:24.618 --> 00:22:26.209
on direct orders from the...

581
00:22:26.237 --> 00:22:27.828
...President of
the United States.

582
00:22:27.829 --> 00:22:28.996
(CHUCKLING)

583
00:22:28.997 --> 00:22:30.831
It's a matter of urgent national security.

584
00:22:30.832 --> 00:22:32.785
I need you to get on
that chopper right now...

585
00:22:32.813 --> 00:22:34.418
...no questions asked.

586
00:22:34.419 --> 00:22:36.212
Crazy Willie put you up to this?

587
00:22:36.213 --> 00:22:38.283
I'm afraid I don't know Crazy Willie,
sir.

588
00:22:38.753 --> 00:22:40.416
I'm dead serious about this.

589
00:22:40.444 --> 00:22:41.455
(LAUGHING)

590
00:22:42.344 --> 00:22:44.178
- Harry.
- What?

591
00:22:44.179 --> 00:22:46.806
I swear to God,
she never told me her age.

592
00:22:46.807 --> 00:22:48.033
HARRY: It's all right. Relax.

593
00:22:48.062 --> 00:22:49.103
It's about me.

594
00:22:50.286 --> 00:22:51.283
Oh.

595
00:22:51.760 --> 00:22:52.767
Forget it!

596
00:22:56.900 --> 00:22:58.407
All right, General,
I'll go with you.

597
00:22:59.446 --> 00:23:00.642
On one condition.

598
00:23:00.946 --> 00:23:02.571
We're gonna have
to take my daughter along.

599
00:23:05.617 --> 00:23:06.701
What did I do?

600
00:23:06.702 --> 00:23:07.868
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Where you guys takin' her?

601
00:23:07.869 --> 00:23:09.071
Sir, stay right here.

602
00:23:09.595 --> 00:23:10.496
Whoa.

603
00:23:10.497 --> 00:23:12.075
Chick, get him paid!

604
00:23:12.104 --> 00:23:13.129
Get him off the rig!

605
00:23:14.640 --> 00:23:16.241
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

606
00:23:23.432 --> 00:23:24.858
TRUMAN: <i>Mr. Stamper?</i>

607
00:23:24.887 --> 00:23:26.247
Yeah, I'm Harry Stamper.

608
00:23:26.471 --> 00:23:27.646
How you doin'?

609
00:23:27.674 --> 00:23:28.848
Miss Stamper.

610
00:23:28.849 --> 00:23:30.641
I'm Dan Truman,
Executive Director here.

611
00:23:30.642 --> 00:23:32.893
Listen, on behalf of all of us,
I'd really like to apologize...

612
00:23:32.894 --> 00:23:35.688
Apologize. I don't know if we can take
any more apologies, Mr. Truman.

613
00:23:35.689 --> 00:23:37.314
We've been apologized
to for the last...

614
00:23:37.343 --> 00:23:38.691
...18-and-a-half hours.

615
00:23:38.692 --> 00:23:41.068
So if you don't mind, how about
if we just get on with it?

616
00:23:41.069 --> 00:23:43.821
You tell us why we're here
at the NASA Space Center.

617
00:23:43.822 --> 00:23:45.740
We should probably talk alone.

618
00:23:45.741 --> 00:23:48.659
Mr. Truman, I don't keep
any secrets from my daughter, Grace.

619
00:23:48.660 --> 00:23:50.619
So whether you tell her now
or I tell her later,

620
00:23:50.620 --> 00:23:52.079
she's gonna find out
one way or the other.

621
00:23:52.080 --> 00:23:53.587
So, why don't we
just get on with it?

622
00:23:53.957 --> 00:23:56.208
TRUMAN: <i>So when the Rogue
comet hit the asteroid belt,</i>

623
00:23:56.209 --> 00:23:58.169
<i>it sent shrapnel right for us.</i>

624
00:23:58.170 --> 00:24:00.921
For the next 15 days,
the Earth's in a shooting gallery.

625
00:24:00.922 --> 00:24:02.791
Even if the asteroid itself...

626
00:24:02.819 --> 00:24:05.092
...hits the water, it's still hitting land.

627
00:24:05.093 --> 00:24:07.762
It'll flash boil millions
of gallons of seawater

628
00:24:07.763 --> 00:24:09.678
and slam into the ocean bedrock.

629
00:24:10.265 --> 00:24:11.975
Now, if it's a Pacific
Ocean impact...

630
00:24:12.004 --> 00:24:13.335
...which we think it will be,

631
00:24:13.769 --> 00:24:15.991
<i>it'll create a tidal
wave three miles high,</i>

632
00:24:16.772 --> 00:24:18.397
<i>traveling at 1,000 miles an hour</i>

633
00:24:18.398 --> 00:24:20.858
<i>covering California
and washing up in Denver.</i>

634
00:24:21.921 --> 00:24:24.616
TRUMAN: <i>Japan's gone.
Australia's wiped out.</i>

635
00:24:25.405 --> 00:24:27.643
Half the world's population
will be incinerated...

636
00:24:27.671 --> 00:24:28.407
...by the heat blast.

637
00:24:28.408 --> 00:24:30.517
The rest'll freeze to death
from nuclear winter.

638
00:24:31.453 --> 00:24:32.898
(SOFTLY) That's unbelievable.

639
00:24:34.807 --> 00:24:36.703
Well, actually, this
is as real as it gets.

640
00:24:37.847 --> 00:24:39.151
(SWEEPING MUSIC PLAYING)

641
00:24:40.040 --> 00:24:41.829
Well, it's coming right now.

642
00:24:42.977 --> 00:24:45.437
Right for us at
22,000 miles an hour.

643
00:24:46.149 --> 00:24:48.001
Not a soul on Earth
can hide from it.

644
00:24:49.122 --> 00:24:50.535
(EXPLOSIONS)

645
00:24:52.327 --> 00:24:53.769
(TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYS)

646
00:24:59.105 --> 00:25:00.313
(SIGNAL BEEPING)

647
00:25:03.156 --> 00:25:04.273
(SIGHS)

648
00:25:04.852 --> 00:25:06.821
I take it you're not
alerting everyone like this.

649
00:25:07.262 --> 00:25:09.660
Nobody knows.
That's the way it stays.

650
00:25:10.270 --> 00:25:11.877
For the next ten
days, there are only...

651
00:25:11.906 --> 00:25:13.327
...nine telescopes in the world

652
00:25:13.328 --> 00:25:15.452
that can spot the asteroid,
and we control eight of 'em.

653
00:25:15.914 --> 00:25:18.609
The president's classified
this information top secret.

654
00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:20.709
If news like this got out,

655
00:25:20.710 --> 00:25:22.745
there'd be an overnight
breakdown of basic...

656
00:25:22.773 --> 00:25:24.213
...social services worldwide.

657
00:25:24.300 --> 00:25:26.874
Rioting, mass
religious hysteria...

658
00:25:27.141 --> 00:25:28.975
...total chaos,
you can imagine.

659
00:25:29.678 --> 00:25:31.531
Basically the worst
parts of the Bible.

660
00:25:35.385 --> 00:25:37.201
Six billion people
on the planet.

661
00:25:38.728 --> 00:25:40.273
Why'd you guys call me?

662
00:25:41.523 --> 00:25:42.648
<i>We need you to prep the team</i>

663
00:25:42.649 --> 00:25:44.400
- <i>we're sending up.</i>
- HARRY: <i>Up?</i>

664
00:25:44.401 --> 00:25:45.693
We'll send them to the asteroid,

665
00:25:45.694 --> 00:25:48.237
they'll land, drill a hole,
they'll drop some nukes,

666
00:25:48.238 --> 00:25:51.031
take off and detonate,
if we can fix this equipment problem.

667
00:25:51.032 --> 00:25:53.400
QUINCY: The drilling
unit's a prototype...

668
00:25:53.428 --> 00:25:55.832
...we've been building
for the Mars project.

669
00:25:55.871 --> 00:25:56.902
You, uh...

670
00:25:57.641 --> 00:25:59.011
...You might recognize the rig.

671
00:26:00.542 --> 00:26:02.410
Yeah, well, I guess
I should recognize it.

672
00:26:03.167 --> 00:26:04.253
It's my design.

673
00:26:04.504 --> 00:26:05.589
(MAN CHATTERING OVER PA)

674
00:26:05.797 --> 00:26:06.941
(HELICOPTER ENGINE WHIRRING)

675
00:26:07.174 --> 00:26:09.119
HARRY: Did you steal a
key to the Patent Office?

676
00:26:09.384 --> 00:26:10.439
TRUMAN: Yeah, basically.

677
00:26:10.635 --> 00:26:11.744
Let me get this straight.

678
00:26:12.517 --> 00:26:13.804
I got pulled off an oil rig,

679
00:26:13.805 --> 00:26:15.489
flown halfway
around the world...

680
00:26:15.517 --> 00:26:17.099
...because you
stole my drill design.

681
00:26:17.100 --> 00:26:18.759
Couldn't read
the plans right...

682
00:26:18.787 --> 00:26:20.661
...and did a pisspoor
job of putting it together.

683
00:26:20.903 --> 00:26:23.262
- Patents don't apply to outer space.
- Shut up, Quincy.

684
00:26:23.565 --> 00:26:25.196
It's not going to Mars anymore.

685
00:26:25.224 --> 00:26:27.067
It's gonna try to save this planet.

686
00:26:27.068 --> 00:26:28.783
And we need to know
what's wrong with it pretty quick.

687
00:26:29.196 --> 00:26:31.238
You said we did a bad job
of putting it together?

688
00:26:31.411 --> 00:26:34.215
No, I said you did a pisspoor
job of putting it together.

689
00:26:34.826 --> 00:26:36.944
First of all, you got the
flow system all reversed.

690
00:26:37.088 --> 00:26:38.185
Let me guess.

691
00:26:38.595 --> 00:26:40.942
You've been tearin' up rotors
and you can't figure out why.

692
00:26:41.541 --> 00:26:42.666
Yeah, that's right.

693
00:26:42.667 --> 00:26:44.943
Well, that's because your
cams are all wrong, Mr. Wizard.

694
00:26:45.545 --> 00:26:46.982
Who's been
operating this thing?

695
00:26:47.964 --> 00:26:48.974
Right there.

696
00:26:49.497 --> 00:26:50.549
We've actually...

697
00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:52.615
We've had them training
for eight months solid now.

698
00:26:52.844 --> 00:26:53.969
Eight whole months?

699
00:26:54.610 --> 00:26:56.986
- Well, pretty much, yeah.
- Well, gee whiz.

700
00:26:57.015 --> 00:26:59.391
Well, this is the team
that has to do the job up there.

701
00:26:59.392 --> 00:27:01.061
We need you to
train them down here.

702
00:27:01.561 --> 00:27:03.053
Well, Mr. Stamper,
what do you think?

703
00:27:03.605 --> 00:27:05.013
You know, drilling's a science.

704
00:27:05.041 --> 00:27:06.041
It's an art.

705
00:27:06.274 --> 00:27:08.901
I'm a third generation driller,
doin' it all my life.

706
00:27:08.902 --> 00:27:11.278
I still haven't got it all figured out.

707
00:27:11.279 --> 00:27:13.146
I assume you sent for
me because somebody...

708
00:27:13.174 --> 00:27:14.435
...told you I was the best.

709
00:27:14.991 --> 00:27:17.349
Well, I'm only the best
because I work with the best.

710
00:27:17.619 --> 00:27:20.353
You don't trust the men you're
working with, you're as good as dead.

711
00:27:21.456 --> 00:27:23.627
Now you wanna send
these boys into space, fine.

712
00:27:23.959 --> 00:27:25.362
I'm sure they'll make good astronauts,

713
00:27:25.710 --> 00:27:27.596
but they don't knowjack about drillin'.

714
00:27:28.629 --> 00:27:30.097
What's your contingency plan?

715
00:27:30.176 --> 00:27:31.257
Contingency plan?

716
00:27:31.258 --> 00:27:33.825
Your backup plan. You gotta have
some kind of backup plan, right?

717
00:27:34.250 --> 00:27:35.636
No, we don't have a backup plan.

718
00:27:35.637 --> 00:27:37.346
- This is it.
- This is the best that you could...

719
00:27:37.347 --> 00:27:38.633
That the government...

720
00:27:38.662 --> 00:27:40.711
...The U.S. government can come up with.

721
00:27:41.142 --> 00:27:43.445
I mean, you're NASA
for cryin' out loud!

722
00:27:43.474 --> 00:27:44.520
You put a man on the moon!

723
00:27:44.521 --> 00:27:45.887
You're geniuses!
You're the guys that...

724
00:27:45.915 --> 00:27:47.554
...think this shit up!

725
00:27:47.857 --> 00:27:50.484
I'm sure you got a team of men
sittin' around somewhere right now,

726
00:27:50.485 --> 00:27:52.732
just thinkin' shit up
and somebody backin' them up.

727
00:27:52.946 --> 00:27:54.154
You tell me
you don't have a backup plan,

728
00:27:54.155 --> 00:27:55.698
that these eight Boy Scouts right here,

729
00:27:55.699 --> 00:27:57.902
that is the world's hope,
that's what you're tellin' me?

730
00:27:58.480 --> 00:27:59.481
Yeah.

731
00:27:59.628 --> 00:28:01.277
Oh, Jesus!

732
00:28:01.659 --> 00:28:02.659
Damn it!

733
00:28:02.998 --> 00:28:04.864
We're a little short on time here.

734
00:28:05.454 --> 00:28:06.620
Will you help us?

735
00:28:10.964 --> 00:28:12.354
All they gotta do is drill?

736
00:28:12.557 --> 00:28:13.642
That's it.

737
00:28:13.800 --> 00:28:16.299
No spacewalkin',
no crazy astronaut stuff.

738
00:28:16.670 --> 00:28:17.674
Just drill.

739
00:28:19.424 --> 00:28:21.682
HARRY: <i>How many men were you
plannin' on takin' up there?</i>

740
00:28:22.058 --> 00:28:24.184
We're sendin' up
two shuttles, two teams.

741
00:28:24.239 --> 00:28:26.252
If I do this, I'm gonna
wanna take my own men.

742
00:28:26.521 --> 00:28:27.573
You got it.

743
00:28:28.905 --> 00:28:30.478
TRUMAN: So you're
saying you'll help us?

744
00:28:31.873 --> 00:28:32.878
Yes, sir.

745
00:28:33.737 --> 00:28:34.737
Thanks.

746
00:28:42.004 --> 00:28:44.379
I just don't trust anybody
else to do it, that's all.

747
00:28:47.042 --> 00:28:48.043
(SIREN WAILING)

748
00:28:48.209 --> 00:28:49.418
No, Mrs. Curlene.

749
00:28:49.419 --> 00:28:51.160
It's Harry Stamper!

750
00:28:51.188 --> 00:28:54.219
You see Bear, you tell
him Harry's lookin' for him.

751
00:28:54.424 --> 00:28:56.717
Those guys get off this rig, they scatter.

752
00:28:56.718 --> 00:28:58.594
Jayotis Kerleen Bear.

753
00:28:58.595 --> 00:29:00.443
Probably the only
black man on a big dog...

754
00:29:00.472 --> 00:29:02.337
...in Kadoka, South Dakota.

755
00:29:02.856 --> 00:29:04.286
Come and get Papa Bear!

756
00:29:07.395 --> 00:29:08.677
GRACE: Uh, Max.

757
00:29:09.197 --> 00:29:10.699
You got a weight
