SHARP: (ON RADIO) <i>Roger,
Freedom. You're looking good.</i>

1624
01:08:39.111 --> 01:08:40.793
<i>You're looking good.</i>

1625
01:08:51.444 --> 01:08:53.653
We have go for Independence.

1626
01:08:53.654 --> 01:08:56.200
WOMAN: (ON RADIO)
<i>Three. Two. One.</i>

1627
01:08:56.532 --> 01:08:58.185
MAN: <i>Independence,
we have booster ignition.</i>

1628
01:08:58.367 --> 01:08:59.526
(CONTINUES CHATTERING)

1629
01:08:59.827 --> 01:09:00.825
We have liftoff.

1630
01:09:01.245 --> 01:09:02.888
We are cooking, Houston.

1631
01:09:03.283 --> 01:09:04.479
(ENGINES ROARING)

1632
01:09:24.852 --> 01:09:25.869
<i>Houston!</i>

1633
01:09:25.898 --> 01:09:27.520
The tower's clear.
They're all yours.

1634
01:09:27.521 --> 01:09:28.542
(ALL CHEERING)

1635
01:09:29.356 --> 01:09:30.543
(SHUTTLES ROARING LOUDLY)

1636
01:09:30.816 --> 01:09:32.484
Heads up, everybody. They're ours now.

1637
01:09:32.485 --> 01:09:33.818
All engines are go.

1638
01:09:33.819 --> 01:09:35.904
Keep a sharp eye out on both of 'em.

1639
01:09:35.905 --> 01:09:37.163
(RADIO CHATTER CONTINUES)

1640
01:09:43.037 --> 01:09:44.552
SHARP: <i>Start roll maneuver.</i>

1641
01:09:55.633 --> 01:09:57.050
Two good roll programs.

1642
01:09:57.051 --> 01:09:58.927
- One down.
- Independence, we have max cue.

1643
01:09:58.928 --> 01:10:00.832
Roger, Control.
We are a max cue.

1644
01:10:02.933 --> 01:10:03.941
S.R.B. sep...

1645
01:10:03.970 --> 01:10:05.097
(ENGINES ROARING)

1646
01:10:09.605 --> 01:10:11.245
We are single-engine, press, demi-go.

1647
01:10:11.482 --> 01:10:12.888
<i>Copy, press, demi-go.</i>

1648
01:10:13.192 --> 01:10:15.245
Houston, this is
a kick-ass ride!

1649
01:10:21.450 --> 01:10:22.613
<i>Freedom, this is Houston.</i>

1650
01:10:22.641 --> 01:10:24.369
<i>Main engine cut out on schedule. Out.</i>

1651
01:10:24.370 --> 01:10:25.623
(ENGINES SLOWING SOFTLY)

1652
01:10:34.171 --> 01:10:36.729
<i>Freedom, stats are good.</i>

1653
01:10:40.511 --> 01:10:42.887
<i>Independence,
telemetry is up and running.</i>

1654
01:10:42.888 --> 01:10:44.097
Oh, my God.

1655
01:10:44.098 --> 01:10:48.059
This is space! Course, we're just
in the beginning part of space.

1656
01:10:48.060 --> 01:10:50.562
We... We haven't gotten
to outer space yet.

1657
01:10:50.563 --> 01:10:52.856
Roger, Houston. We have a visual
on the Russian space station.

1658
01:10:52.857 --> 01:10:55.070
Initiating retro burn.

1659
01:10:56.527 --> 01:10:58.570
<i>Gentlemen, remember
the Russian space station</i>

1660
01:10:58.571 --> 01:11:00.280
<i>has been up there for 11 years.</i>

1661
01:11:00.281 --> 01:11:02.240
<i>Most of us don't have cars that old.</i>

1662
01:11:02.241 --> 01:11:03.283
<i>Now, the cosmonaut on board</i>

1663
01:11:03.284 --> 01:11:06.974
<i>has been on that tin can
for 18 months, alone.</i>

1664
01:11:09.331 --> 01:11:11.958
TRUMAN: <i>So don't be
surprised if he's a little... off.</i>

1665
01:11:11.959 --> 01:11:13.334
<i>Independence, we're gonna put you...</i>

1666
01:11:13.335 --> 01:11:15.253
All right, crew.
Let's exit these flight suits.

1667
01:11:15.254 --> 01:11:16.284
(LAUGHING HAPPILY)

1668
01:11:17.173 --> 01:11:18.923
(IN RUSSIAN ACCENT) Hello.

1669
01:11:18.924 --> 01:11:22.886
This is Russian space station.
Can you hear me?

1670
01:11:22.887 --> 01:11:23.928
(SPEAKS RUSSIAN)

1671
01:11:23.929 --> 01:11:25.930
We copy, Russian space station.
This is Houston.

1672
01:11:25.931 --> 01:11:29.726
I'm ready to fire my thrusters any time.

1673
01:11:29.727 --> 01:11:33.021
- <i>Stand by.</i>
- Okay. I'm not going anywhere.

1674
01:11:33.022 --> 01:11:35.773
<i>We have a go.
Initiate gravitational spin.</i>

1675
01:11:35.774 --> 01:11:36.908
(MAN CHATTERING
ON RADIO)

1676
01:11:37.109 --> 01:11:38.276
(THRUSTERS FIRING)

1677
01:11:43.282 --> 01:11:45.408
<i>You are maxed
at 40-percent spin.</i>

1678
01:11:45.409 --> 01:11:46.436
(LEV MOANS)

1679
01:11:47.745 --> 01:11:50.155
Okay, Houston.

1680
01:11:50.623 --> 01:11:55.423
I can feel I'm having gravity.

1681
01:11:55.502 --> 01:11:58.296
All right, gentlemen.
We're gonna dock in a minute.

1682
01:11:58.297 --> 01:11:59.464
Now, the Russian space station

1683
01:11:59.465 --> 01:12:00.924
- has fired her rockets...
- Whee!

1684
01:12:00.925 --> 01:12:03.092
...to simulate gravity
and let us work faster.

1685
01:12:03.093 --> 01:12:05.136
It's gonna make you queasy,
so prepare yourself.

1686
01:12:05.137 --> 01:12:06.138
Well, it's about time.

1687
01:12:06.215 --> 01:12:07.722
I haven't thrown up in about an hour.

1688
01:12:07.723 --> 01:12:08.794
(LAUGHING)

1689
01:12:12.603 --> 01:12:16.022
Initiating first phase
of docking procedure.

1690
01:12:16.023 --> 01:12:19.123
- Switching to manual.
- Manual override.

1691
01:12:24.406 --> 01:12:28.326
One foot per second. Let's take this
slow and do it right, folks.

1692
01:12:28.327 --> 01:12:29.999
Twenty feet.

1693
01:12:30.829 --> 01:12:31.897
(SIGNAL BEEPING)

1694
01:12:32.498 --> 01:12:33.748
Ten feet.

1695
01:12:33.749 --> 01:12:36.061
Looking good on radar.

1696
01:12:36.919 --> 01:12:38.542
Five feet.

1697
01:12:39.046 --> 01:12:40.652
(CLANKING, HISSING)

1698
01:12:42.174 --> 01:12:43.621
Locks are engaged.

1699
01:12:43.649 --> 01:12:45.421
Fuel teams, let's go.

1700
01:12:46.637 --> 01:12:48.972
Freedom, telemetry
is looking good.

1701
01:12:48.973 --> 01:12:50.039
(HISSING)

1702
01:12:50.140 --> 01:12:51.975
We have soft dock.

1703
01:12:51.976 --> 01:12:54.878
SHARP: Fuel teams,
prepare to unload.

1704
01:12:58.732 --> 01:13:00.525
All right, gentlemen, watch your heads.

1705
01:13:00.526 --> 01:13:02.788
Let's go, Independence.

