1957
01:25:07.085 --> 01:25:08.836
<i>Independence, try to maintain
your present heading.</i>

1958
01:25:08.837 --> 01:25:10.004
<i>You've got a target L.Z.</i>

1959
01:25:10.005 --> 01:25:12.297
TUCKER: There's too much debris!
We gotta peel off!

1960
01:25:12.298 --> 01:25:13.309
Negative!

1961
01:25:14.009 --> 01:25:15.020
(CRASHING LOUDLY)

1962
01:25:16.770 --> 01:25:17.777
We're hit!

1963
01:25:20.682 --> 01:25:21.864
Mayday, mayday!

1964
01:25:21.975 --> 01:25:23.934
I've lost main thrusters.
Get 'em back up!

1965
01:25:23.935 --> 01:25:25.148
Mayday, Houston, mayday!

1966
01:25:25.176 --> 01:25:26.353
We've lost R.C.S. thrusters!

1967
01:25:26.354 --> 01:25:27.809
Mayday, Freedom, mayday!

1968
01:25:28.148 --> 01:25:30.090
We are out of control!
We are going down!

1969
01:25:30.119 --> 01:25:31.196
Do you read me?

1970
01:25:31.294 --> 01:25:32.731
Freedom, we are going down!

1971
01:25:39.200 --> 01:25:40.309
(BOTH EXCLAIM)

1972
01:25:42.245 --> 01:25:43.328
(ALL SHOUT)

1973
01:25:43.329 --> 01:25:44.589
(THRUSTERS ROARING)

1974
01:25:46.082 --> 01:25:47.124
We're gonna hit!

1975
01:25:47.125 --> 01:25:48.203
(BLIPPING)

1976
01:25:50.559 --> 01:25:51.645
(CRASHING)

1977
01:25:52.579 --> 01:25:53.598
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

1978
01:25:57.594 --> 01:25:59.669
Everybody, go to
your own life support!

1979
01:25:59.969 --> 01:26:01.794
Lock yourself in the cargo bay!

1980
01:26:03.850 --> 01:26:05.115
We are going down!

1981
01:26:05.310 --> 01:26:06.516
DAVIS: <i>Houston!</i>

1982
01:26:06.545 --> 01:26:07.688
<i>Houston, we are going down!</i>

1983
01:26:07.717 --> 01:26:09.104
<i>We have lost control!</i>

1984
01:26:09.105 --> 01:26:10.456
I can't get it on!

1985
01:26:13.026 --> 01:26:14.026
Good luck, Freedom.

1986
01:26:14.611 --> 01:26:16.269
Oh, my God, this is it.

1987
01:26:16.744 --> 01:26:17.862
(GLASS BREAKING SOFTLY)

1988
01:26:18.656 --> 01:26:19.690
(SIGNAL BLIPPING)

1989
01:26:19.873 --> 01:26:20.893
(BOTH SCREAMING)

1990
01:26:25.007 --> 01:26:26.312
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

1991
01:26:32.962 --> 01:26:34.093
(LEV SHOUTING IN RUSSIAN)

1992
01:26:41.300 --> 01:26:42.446
(EXPLODING)

1993
01:26:47.498 --> 01:26:48.520
(CLANGING)

1994
01:26:50.686 --> 01:26:51.863
(EXPLOSION)

1995
01:26:54.692 --> 01:26:55.699
(OSCAR SCREAMING)

1996
01:26:57.320 --> 01:26:58.504
(BANGING LOUDLY)

1997
01:27:07.064 --> 01:27:08.259
Sharp, what the hell is that?

1998
01:27:08.288 --> 01:27:09.837
- Is that the Independence?
- (BANGING)

1999
01:27:15.380 --> 01:27:17.411
SHARP: <i>Houston,
Independence is a dead stick.</i>

2000
01:27:17.549 --> 01:27:18.567
<i>They're not gonna make it.</i>

2001
01:27:19.848 --> 01:27:21.239
(ENGINES FIRING)

2002
01:27:31.563 --> 01:27:34.564
Houston,
Independence has gone down.

2003
01:27:46.202 --> 01:27:48.620
When I touch this baby down,
full reverse thrust.

2004
01:27:48.621 --> 01:27:50.706
- Fires on your right, Sharp!
- Reversing the thrusters!

2005
01:27:50.707 --> 01:27:52.011
(THRUSTERS FIRING)

2006
01:27:52.834 --> 01:27:54.355
Hang tight!
Hang tight!

2007
01:27:55.784 --> 01:27:57.713
Houston, we overshot
our landing field.

2008
01:27:57.940 --> 01:27:59.214
We overshot
our landing field.

2009
01:27:59.215 --> 01:28:00.987
Oh, no!

2010
01:28:06.264 --> 01:28:07.268
(GRUNTING)

2011
01:28:08.516 --> 01:28:09.582
(ICE SMASHING)

2012
01:28:14.397 --> 01:28:15.398
(SHOUTING)

2013
01:28:21.362 --> 01:28:22.745
- God!
- (SCREAMING)

2014
01:28:25.491 --> 01:28:26.617
(CRASHING STOPS)

2015
01:28:27.618 --> 01:28:28.768
(PANTING HEAVILY)

2016
01:28:31.998 --> 01:28:33.081
(WHIMPERING SHAKILY)

2017
01:28:34.120 --> 01:28:36.026
(PANTING HEAVILY)

2018
01:28:38.880 --> 01:28:40.633
Initiate system
light system check.

2019
01:28:40.661 --> 01:28:42.716
Make sure we can
still get off this rock.

2020
01:28:42.717 --> 01:28:45.260
Our electrical system is screwed.
I'm going to back-up.

2021
01:28:45.261 --> 01:28:47.137
Fuel seals check. Engine seals check.

2022
01:28:47.138 --> 01:28:50.483
- Oh, God. Oh!
- Pressure seals check.

2023
01:28:53.311 --> 01:28:54.394
Anyone hurt?

2024
01:28:54.395 --> 01:28:55.613
(PANTING HEAVILY)

2025
01:28:56.141 --> 01:28:57.248
Where's...

2026
01:28:58.358 --> 01:28:59.943
Where's the other shuttle?

2027
01:28:59.971 --> 01:29:02.110
What happened to the other shuttle?

2028
01:29:02.111 --> 01:29:04.613
Independence is off the grid.

2029
01:29:04.614 --> 01:29:05.697
"Off the grid"?

2030
01:29:05.698 --> 01:29:08.018
What are you, a freakin' cyborg?
What does that mean?

2031
01:29:08.993 --> 01:29:11.135
Hey, you saw it yourself, right?

2032
01:29:11.704 --> 01:29:12.698
They're gone.

2033
01:29:14.582 --> 01:29:16.670
<i>Come in, Freedom. This is
CAPCOM Houston.</i>

2034
01:29:16.698 --> 01:29:18.168
Freedom, come in.

2035
01:29:18.169 --> 01:29:20.729
This is CAPCOM Houston.
Come in, Freedom.

2036
01:29:22.215 --> 01:29:23.840
- God!
- Let's just ask God

2037
01:29:23.841 --> 01:29:25.143
to take care of our friends.

2038
01:29:27.637 --> 01:29:28.791
May they rest in peace.

2039
01:29:30.890 --> 01:29:31.901
Amen.

2040
01:29:32.392 --> 01:29:33.502
(COMPUTERS BLIPPING)

2041
01:29:40.149 --> 01:29:41.252
We got eight hours.

2042
01:29:42.277 --> 01:29:43.278
(GASPS)

2043
01:29:43.361 --> 01:29:44.775
Let's get this job
done and go home.

2044
01:29:46.447 --> 01:29:47.531
Nothin'.

2045
01:29:47.532 --> 01:29:49.500
Come on, Watts,
Sharp, somebody.

2046
01:29:50.368 --> 01:29:52.729
This is CAPCOM Houston.

2047
01:29:53.769 --> 01:29:54.776
<i>Come in, Freedom.</i>

2048
01:29:55.472 --> 01:29:56.559
<i>Freedom, come in.</i>

2049
01:29:56.588 --> 01:29:57.711
<i>This is CAPCOM Houston.</i>

2050
01:29:59.627 --> 01:30:00.837
Maybe you shouldn't be here.

2051
01:30:01.796 --> 01:30:04.214
I don't have
anywhere else to go.

2052
01:30:04.215 --> 01:30:05.166
<i>Freedom, come in.</i>

2053
01:30:05.194 --> 01:30:06.485
<i>This is CAPCOM Houston.</i>

2054
01:30:08.062 --> 01:30:09.881
HARRY: All right, let's
get the tools unpacked

2055
01:30:09.909 --> 01:30:11.013
and fire up the Armadillo.

2056
01:30:11.014 --> 01:30:12.207
We're not getting a damn thing

2057
01:30:12.235 --> 01:30:13.307
on the inertial nav system.

2058
01:30:13.308 --> 01:30:15.086
- I know where we are.
- Please step away.

2059
01:30:15.893 --> 01:30:17.311
Radio signal's dead.

2060
01:30:17.312 --> 01:30:19.062
I'm flipping the backup generator.

2061
01:30:19.063 --> 01:30:20.483
Radio signal's
gonna be cut in half

2062
01:30:20.515 --> 01:30:21.648
till we get main power back.

2063
01:30:21.649 --> 01:30:24.033
We're in segment
202, lateral grid 9,

2064
01:30:24.065 --> 01:30:26.449
site 15H-32, give
or take a few yards.

2065
01:30:27.238 --> 01:30:30.907
Captain America here
blew the landing by 26 miles.

2066
01:30:30.908 --> 01:30:33.243
How the hell do you know that?

2067
01:30:33.244 --> 01:30:35.078
Because I'm a genius.

2068
01:30:35.079 --> 01:30:36.163
The gauges will not read.

2069
01:30:36.164 --> 01:30:36.890
They're all peaked,

2070
01:30:36.900 --> 01:30:38.622
like we're plugged into
some magnetic field.

2071
01:30:38.624 --> 01:30:40.500
Well, who on this spaceship
wants to know why?

2072
01:30:40.501 --> 01:30:43.045
- SHARP: By all means.
- The reason we were shooting for grid 8

2073
01:30:43.046 --> 01:30:45.974
is because thermographics
indicated that grid 9

2074
01:30:46.006 --> 01:30:47.846
was compressed iron ferrite.

2075
01:30:48.885 --> 01:30:51.270
Which means that you landed us

2076
01:30:51.302 --> 01:30:53.067
on a goddamn iron plate.

2077
01:30:55.099 --> 01:30:56.141
All right. Well, you heard the man.

2078
01:30:56.142 --> 01:30:57.504
Let's wheel out the remote satellite link.

2079
01:30:57.536 --> 01:30:58.143
We need that radio.

2080
01:30:58.144 --> 01:30:59.853
Oh, God, please tell me
we still got one of 'em.

2081
01:30:59.854 --> 01:31:01.013
(COMPUTERS BEEPING)

2082
01:31:02.899 --> 01:31:04.608
MAN: <i>Independence has flat-lined.</i>

2083
01:31:04.609 --> 01:31:05.679
(WEEPING)

2084
01:31:35.430 --> 01:31:36.728
(GRUNTING)

2085
01:31:45.650 --> 01:31:46.712
<i>Oh.</i>

2086
01:31:49.654 --> 01:31:51.677
<i>Oscar! Oscar!</i>

2087
01:31:54.242 --> 01:31:55.958
(CRYING) <i>Oh, God!</i>

2088
01:31:59.497 --> 01:32:00.739
<i>Hello!</i>

2089
01:32:00.992 --> 01:32:03.114
<i>Anyone! Is anyone else alive?</i>

2090
01:32:04.108 --> 01:32:05.935
<i>Somebody, help me!</i>

2091
01:32:07.794 --> 01:32:08.911
LEV: <i>A.J.!</i>

2092
01:32:10.591 --> 01:32:11.685
<i>Where are you?</i>

2093
01:32:12.301 --> 01:32:13.458
LEV: <i>I'm here.</i>

2094
01:32:14.554 --> 01:32:15.626
(GRUNTING)

2095
01:32:18.224 --> 01:32:20.333
<i>Lev, there's no one else.</i>

2096
01:32:21.394 --> 01:32:22.388
<i>There's no one else.</i>

2097
01:32:22.812 --> 01:32:24.099
<i>I know.</i>

2098
01:32:24.397 --> 01:32:26.414
BEAR: <i>Oh, man.</i>

2099
01:32:26.816 --> 01:32:29.495
- A.J.: <i>Bear, where are you?</i>
- BEAR: <i>A.J.? A.J.?</i>

2100
01:32:31.571 --> 01:32:32.941
BEAR: <i>I'm in the shuttle, man.</i>

2101
01:32:33.739 --> 01:32:34.823
(GRUNTS)

2102
01:32:34.824 --> 01:32:36.841
<i>Are you all right?</i>

2103
01:32:36.868 --> 01:32:38.401
<i>I'm so glad to see you, man.</i>

2104
01:32:39.328 --> 01:32:41.034
<i>I never thought I'd be so happy</i>

2105
01:32:41.062 --> 01:32:42.269
<i>to see your ugly face.</i>

2106
01:32:42.707 --> 01:32:45.125
Houston, do you read? This is Freedom.

2107
01:32:45.126 --> 01:32:46.501
SHARP: Check your thrusters.

2108
01:32:46.502 --> 01:32:48.295
WATTS: Houston, do you copy?

2109
01:32:48.296 --> 01:32:50.165
SHARP: Is everyone good to go?

2110
01:33:00.892 --> 01:33:02.268
Wow.

2111
01:33:12.695 --> 01:33:15.548
HARRY: Down here!
In the valley!

2112
01:33:16.073 --> 01:33:19.159
This place is like
Dr. Seuss's worst nightmare.

2113
01:33:19.160 --> 01:33:21.034
Let's get the remote satellite.

2114
01:33:21.066 --> 01:33:23.244
We'll get better
reception up there.

2115
01:33:23.915 --> 01:33:25.582
HARRY: Bring Max down.

2116
01:33:25.583 --> 01:33:27.298
Watch yourself
through here, Max.

2117
01:33:27.330 --> 01:33:29.044
There're a couple big fissures.

2118
01:33:29.045 --> 01:33:30.378
To the left!

2119
01:33:30.379 --> 01:33:32.692
Bring it to the left!

2120
01:33:37.595 --> 01:33:39.012
HARRY: Rockhound,
you come on down here

2121
01:33:39.013 --> 01:33:41.681
and take some readings
down in the flat spot.

2122
01:33:41.682 --> 01:33:42.875
(BEEPING)

2123
01:33:43.976 --> 01:33:45.797
Iron ferrite.

2124
01:33:48.648 --> 01:33:50.232
I have fire.

2125
01:33:50.233 --> 01:33:52.374
HARRY: Watts, I'm comin' back.

2126
01:33:52.406 --> 01:33:53.109
Stand by.

2127
01:33:53.110 --> 01:33:55.324
Mostly iron, Rockhound.

2128
01:33:55.446 --> 01:33:57.239
God, I hate knowing everything.

2129
01:33:57.240 --> 01:34:00.033
We couldn't have picked
a worse spot to drill.

2130
01:34:00.034 --> 01:34:01.929
Well, I can pretty
much guarantee

2131
01:34:01.961 --> 01:34:04.204
it's not gonna be
thicker than 50 feet.

2132
01:34:04.205 --> 01:34:07.895
- How do you figure that?
- 'Cause if it is, we're screwed.

2133
01:34:09.377 --> 01:34:12.128
- Max, you good?
- Yeah. Just makin' hole.

2134
01:34:12.129 --> 01:34:13.588
Turn it around.

2135
01:34:13.589 --> 01:34:16.049
MAX: Friggin' outer space.

2136
01:34:18.135 --> 01:34:19.759
It's good.

2137
01:34:26.561 --> 01:34:28.401
All right. We're in.
Another light.

2138
01:34:28.433 --> 01:34:30.272
We're cuttin'
through pretty good.

2139
01:34:30.273 --> 01:34:33.692
There's some stuff in here
I ain't never seen.

2140
01:34:33.693 --> 01:34:35.694
All right, let's punch it down!

2141
01:34:35.695 --> 01:34:36.762
(METAL CREAKING)

2142
01:34:37.163 --> 01:34:38.388
Hey, Harry, did you see that?

2143
01:34:38.420 --> 01:34:40.156
Yeah, Max, I see it.
I see it. What is it?

2144
01:34:40.157 --> 01:34:41.491
We lost the bite in the bit.

2145
01:34:41.492 --> 01:34:43.827
All right. Back it off. Back it off.

2146
01:34:43.828 --> 01:34:45.287
Goddamn it!

2147
01:34:45.288 --> 01:34:47.539
Sounds like we twisted a shank.
Back it out of there, Max.

2148
01:34:47.540 --> 01:34:50.049
Good. Good. Hold 'er there.

2149
01:34:53.963 --> 01:34:57.257
Wow, this is a goddamn Greek tragedy.

2150
01:34:57.258 --> 01:34:59.509
We've all seen
broken drill heads before.

2151
01:34:59.510 --> 01:35:01.344
Not after ten feet.

2152
01:35:01.345 --> 01:35:04.180
- I never seen one.
- Well, now you've seen one.

2153
01:35:04.181 --> 01:35:07.133
- What do you want?
- Unpack the Judge.

2154
01:35:09.186 --> 01:35:11.105
A.J.: Bear, Lev.

2155
01:35:11.689 --> 01:35:15.379
LEV: We're only
three astronauts left now.

2156
01:35:15.401 --> 01:35:17.193
A.J.: We're not astronauts.
We're oil drillers.

2157
01:35:17.194 --> 01:35:19.279
We're not even supposed to be here.

2158
01:35:19.280 --> 01:35:21.739
What? You're not astronaut?

2159
01:35:21.907 --> 01:35:24.784
- I'm getting us outta here. Get in.
- Why?

2160
01:35:24.785 --> 01:35:27.245
Just get in the Armadillo. I have an idea.

2161
01:35:27.246 --> 01:35:29.414
Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?

2162
01:35:29.415 --> 01:35:32.042
Houston, do you copy?
Freedom shuttle has...

2163
01:35:32.043 --> 01:35:33.052
(RADIO STATIC)

2164
01:35:33.753 --> 01:35:36.504
We're gettin'
some scattered video feeds here.

2165
01:35:36.505 --> 01:35:38.715
WATTS: Houston, this is Freedom.
Do you copy?

2166
01:35:38.716 --> 01:35:41.384
- Thank God we have you, Freedom.
- Freedom, this is Houston. Go ahead.

2167
01:35:41.385 --> 01:35:43.970
- Don't lose 'em, Malloy.
- Shut up. I'm getting something.

2168
01:35:43.971 --> 01:35:45.055
Houston, this is Freedom.

2169
01:35:45.056 --> 01:35:46.931
- We have landed safely.
- Where are they?

2170
01:35:46.932 --> 01:35:49.726
We are at site coordinates
approximately 15H-32...

2171
01:35:49.727 --> 01:35:51.561
Okay, I want to know everything
we can about that location.

2172
01:35:51.562 --> 01:35:52.812
- Got it.
- Get it before we lose 'em.

2173
01:35:52.813 --> 01:35:55.065
We're also having electric
and antenna difficulties.

2174
01:35:55.066 --> 01:35:56.399
Walter, get Mechanical on that.

2175
01:35:56.400 --> 01:35:58.443
But we have commenced drilling.

2176
01:35:58.444 --> 01:36:00.445
Stevens, we're losin' him.
Bring it up on four. On four.

2177
01:36:00.446 --> 01:36:04.115
- Come on.
- Shuttle flight capability not yet known.

2178
01:36:04.116 --> 01:36:05.200
- Bump the signal.
- Bumping.

2179
01:36:05.201 --> 01:36:06.576
Houston. Houston.

2180
01:36:06.577 --> 01:36:09.641
We lost 'em. Get 'em back.
Gruber, we need that hookup.

2181
01:36:11.666 --> 01:36:14.273
Show you how we do things
where I come from.

2182
01:36:22.093 --> 01:36:23.666
Hold on!

2183
01:36:25.346 --> 01:36:26.505
(METAL CRUMPLING)

2184
01:36:33.229 --> 01:36:34.852
Seat it.

2185
01:36:35.272 --> 01:36:38.470
All right, get ready. Max, thread it.

2186
01:36:39.443 --> 01:36:41.033
Guys, the clock is tickin'.

2187
01:36:41.065 --> 01:36:42.654
Let's go, go, go, go, go!

2188
01:36:42.655 --> 01:36:44.823
All right! Good! Crank it loose!

2189
01:36:44.824 --> 01:36:47.992
Keep it at 25.
Let's kick a little asteroid butt!

2190
01:36:47.993 --> 01:36:48.661
All right, Chick.

2191
01:36:48.693 --> 01:36:50.286
Give me more torque
on the turbine, huh?

2192
01:36:50.287 --> 01:36:51.321
(DRILL WHINING)

2193
01:36:51.622 --> 01:36:53.123
HARRY: Max, I need some
more power down here!

2194
01:36:53.124 --> 01:36:54.541
- All right, boss.
- Throw it in fourth,

2195
01:36:54.542 --> 01:36:55.792
then drop the hammer.

2196
01:36:55.793 --> 01:36:57.460
Let's drill through this turd.

2197
01:36:57.461 --> 01:36:58.964
HARRY: Come on, boys.
We gotta hop.

2198
01:36:58.996 --> 01:36:59.963
We're fallin' behind.

2199
01:36:59.964 --> 01:37:01.184
Dig, dig, dig.

2200
01:37:01.216 --> 01:37:03.407
Chew this iron bitch up.

2201
01:37:03.801 --> 01:37:05.010
(METAL WHINING)

2202
01:37:08.180 --> 01:37:09.973
- Chick, the tranny's stuck.
- Harry!

2203
01:37:09.974 --> 01:37:11.597
What is it?

2204
01:37:11.976 --> 01:37:13.059
Chick, come on! Help!

2205
01:37:13.060 --> 01:37:14.811
- Release the clutch!
- Pull it up!

2206
01:37:14.812 --> 01:37:17.813
Okay. Well, this thing's not movin'.

2207
01:37:18.357 --> 01:37:21.457
No, no, no!
Shut it down!

2208
01:37:22.445 --> 01:37:23.552
(GROANING)

2209
01:37:28.284 --> 01:37:30.326
This is not workin' out, Harry.

2210
01:37:30.327 --> 01:37:33.663
Oh, are you all right?
- Oh, blew the tranny.

2211
01:37:33.695 --> 01:37:35.127
Blew the tranny.

2212
01:37:35.708 --> 01:37:37.430
Come on, God.

2213
01:37:38.586 --> 01:37:42.276
Just a little help. That's all I'm askin'.

2214
01:37:42.381 --> 01:37:46.120
I think we're close enough.
He might've heard ya.

2215
01:37:48.429 --> 01:37:50.847
Here's the bad news.
Before the asteroid passed the moon,

2216
01:37:50.848 --> 01:37:54.184
her rotation was stable
at 32 degrees on an x axis.

2217
01:37:54.185 --> 01:37:58.438
But now look at this.
The lunar gravity's put her in a spin.

2218
01:37:58.439 --> 01:38:01.983
She's tumbling on all three axes.
This wasn't expected, sir.

2219
01:38:01.984 --> 01:38:04.652
- What does this do for communications?
- Not good.

2220
01:38:04.653 --> 01:38:07.405
We'll have definite contact with
the shuttle for only seven more minutes.

2221
01:38:07.406 --> 01:38:10.283
- After that it's radio darkness.
- For how long?

2222
01:38:10.284 --> 01:38:12.013
And after seven minutes,

2223
01:38:12.041 --> 01:38:14.496
we may never hear
from them again.

2224
01:38:14.497 --> 01:38:16.080
But we're trying to bounce a signal

2225
01:38:16.081 --> 01:38:17.380
off a Russian
military satellite,

2226
01:38:17.408 --> 01:38:18.625
reestablish
contact that way.

2227
01:38:18.626 --> 01:38:20.543
If we lose the shuttle com,

2228
01:38:20.544 --> 01:38:21.844
when do we lose the ability

2229
01:38:21.872 --> 01:38:23.171
to remote
detonate that nuke?

2230
01:38:23.172 --> 01:38:24.575
The weapon remote
receives a signal

2231
01:38:24.603 --> 01:38:25.673
from a Milstar satellite.

2232
01:38:25.674 --> 01:38:27.759
Higher orbit, more powerful transmitter.

2233
01:38:27.760 --> 01:38:29.761
If we've got the shuttle
for seven minutes,

2234
01:38:29.762 --> 01:38:30.957
we can remote detonate

2235
01:38:30.985 --> 01:38:32.180
for an additional five.

2236
01:38:32.181 --> 01:38:34.390
What he's trying to say, General,
is that, uh, in 12 minutes' time,

2237
01:38:34.391 --> 01:38:35.861
you may lose the ability

2238
01:38:35.889 --> 01:38:38.102
to detonate the
nuke... permanently.

2239
01:38:38.103 --> 01:38:40.268
I've got to inform the president.

2240
01:38:41.565 --> 01:38:42.932
Just want to make
sure you know

2241
01:38:42.960 --> 01:38:44.234
we're stuck on an asteroid.

2242
01:38:44.235 --> 01:38:46.236
- Do you know what you're doing now?
- No, no.

2243
01:38:46.237 --> 01:38:49.614
You know what? I have no idea
what I'm doing. I have no idea.

2244
01:38:49.615 --> 01:38:51.991
This button,
I don't know what that does, okay?

2245
01:38:51.992 --> 01:38:54.619
All I know is
that we just crashed back there,

2246
01:38:54.620 --> 01:38:57.580
I lost two of my friends,
we're 25 miles from Harry's shuttle.

2247
01:38:57.581 --> 01:39:00.083
We don't know if he's alive.
We don't know if he can fly.

2248
01:39:00.084 --> 01:39:01.876
All I know is,
there's a beep on this thing

2249
01:39:01.877 --> 01:39:03.636
and I'm trying to get us there.

2250
01:39:10.678 --> 01:39:11.761
[Beeping]

2251
01:39:11.762 --> 01:39:14.123
Let's get it unpacked.

2252
01:39:14.890 --> 01:39:15.932
What's up?

2253
01:39:15.933 --> 01:39:17.097
We're drilling through some

2254
01:39:17.125 --> 01:39:18.726
kind of metal I've
never seen before.

2255
01:39:18.727 --> 01:39:20.066
It's fried two
of our drill bits,

2256
01:39:20.094 --> 01:39:21.771
and now we blew
our first transmission.

2257
01:39:21.772 --> 01:39:22.856
So how deep are we?

2258
01:39:22.857 --> 01:39:24.649
We could use your help
with the transmission, Colonel.

2259
01:39:24.650 --> 01:39:26.137
I have an assessment
report due now.

2260
01:39:26.165 --> 01:39:27.610
We're supposed
to be at 200 feet.

2261
01:39:27.611 --> 01:39:30.446
- So how deep are we?
- Not as deep as we'll be

2262
01:39:30.447 --> 01:39:32.031
when you quit askin' me
these questions

2263
01:39:32.032 --> 01:39:33.700
and help us load this transmission on.

2264
01:39:33.701 --> 01:39:35.034
What is our current depth?

2265
01:39:35.035 --> 01:39:36.911
Our current depth
is not important, Colonel.

2266
01:39:36.912 --> 01:39:38.462
I'll decide
what's important.

2267
01:39:38.490 --> 01:39:40.039
We've got
800 feet to drill.

2268
01:39:40.040 --> 01:39:42.466
You've had two
and a half hours.

2269
01:39:42.494 --> 01:39:43.582
Where are we?

2270
01:39:44.753 --> 01:39:46.622
We're at 57 feet.

2271
01:39:46.964 --> 01:39:48.047
Now, if you're not too busy,

2272
01:39:48.048 --> 01:39:50.425
maybe you can give us a hand
with this transmission.

2273
01:39:50.426 --> 01:39:52.246
Colonel Sharp!

2274
01:39:53.095 --> 01:39:55.113
Get this strapped up.
I'll be right back.

2275
01:39:55.141 --> 01:39:55.889
Colonel Sharp!

2276
01:39:55.890 --> 01:39:57.776
All right. I'm coming through.

2277
01:39:57.804 --> 01:39:59.183
We have contact. Over.

2278
01:39:59.184 --> 01:40:02.234
That's as clear as it's gonna get.

2279
01:40:02.521 --> 01:40:04.814
Houston, this is Freedom. Do you copy?

2280
01:40:04.815 --> 01:40:07.483
Working at a remote satellite link
at this moment.

2281
01:40:07.484 --> 01:40:08.818
- Transmission change.
- Colonel!

2282
01:40:08.819 --> 01:40:11.571
Twenty minutes.
Puts drilling final at ten hours.

2283
01:40:11.572 --> 01:40:15.158
Please advise. That's four hours
past the zero barrier. Please advise.

2284
01:40:15.159 --> 01:40:18.161
What the hell is this? "Zero depth"?

2285
01:40:18.162 --> 01:40:20.997
And where'd this come from?
Who are you talkin' to? Is that Truman?

2286
01:40:20.998 --> 01:40:22.498
Lemme have that phone.
Gimme the phone.

2287
01:40:22.499 --> 01:40:25.543
Truman! Look, this is what happens
when you drill.

2288
01:40:25.544 --> 01:40:27.699
We cannot use
your "U.S. Air Force

2289
01:40:27.727 --> 01:40:29.881
Personnel Only"
drill time card.

2290
01:40:29.882 --> 01:40:32.091
- Who wrote this thing, by the way?
- We're losing coms again.

2291
01:40:32.092 --> 01:40:34.385
Look. Is he getting this?
Does he hear me or...

2292
01:40:34.386 --> 01:40:35.803
- What's wrong with this?
- The com's down.

2293
01:40:35.804 --> 01:40:36.846
What do you mean, "the com's down"?

2294
01:40:36.847 --> 01:40:38.264
SHARP: What do I mean?
I mean we've lost

2295
01:40:38.265 --> 01:40:39.891
- communication to mission control.
- Fine.

2296
01:40:39.892 --> 01:40:41.935
Let's go back to the cargo bay
and get the transmission...

2297
01:40:41.936 --> 01:40:45.355
Harry, guess what. You had your shot.
You didn't do it. You understand me?

2298
01:40:45.356 --> 01:40:47.190
- You can't...
- Why don't you stay here...

2299
01:40:47.191 --> 01:40:48.503
(SHOUTING)

2300
01:40:49.944 --> 01:40:51.986
Write a report, why don't ya?
That'll be...

2301
01:40:51.987 --> 01:40:53.196
(SHOUTING CONTINUES)

2302
01:40:53.697 --> 01:40:55.949
My men and I will go
and get this hole dug!

2303
01:40:55.950 --> 01:40:58.298
You and your
men are the biggest

2304
01:40:58.326 --> 01:41:00.674
mistake in the
history of NASA.

2305
01:41:02.331 --> 01:41:04.974
MAN: We've lost
communication.

2306
01:41:05.002 --> 01:41:05.873
Oh, God.

2307
01:41:07.878 --> 01:41:11.464
We're not lookin'
too good right now.

2308
01:41:11.492 --> 01:41:12.678
No shit.

2309
01:41:13.133 --> 01:41:15.150
We gotta get that radio back up.

2310
01:41:17.221 --> 01:41:20.515
MAN: Mr. President,
it's time to make a decision.

2311
01:41:20.516 --> 01:41:22.775
We can remote
detonate the bomb

2312
01:41:22.803 --> 01:41:25.061
for only another
five minutes.

2313
01:41:25.062 --> 01:41:26.685
[Rings]

2314
01:41:26.730 --> 01:41:30.075
Yes? Kimsey here. Yes, Mr. President.

2315
01:41:30.859 --> 01:41:33.270
Yes, we saw that, too, sir.

2316
01:41:33.570 --> 01:41:36.719
But maybe we should wait until they...

2317
01:41:42.663 --> 01:41:46.451
Dan, get them out of there.

2318
01:41:46.709 --> 01:41:49.168
- Evac right now.
- What's goin' on here?

2319
01:41:49.169 --> 01:41:51.087
I've been ordered
to override the system.

2320
01:41:51.088 --> 01:41:53.695
[Elevator Bells Dinging]

2321
01:41:55.968 --> 01:41:58.280
Well, what is this?

2322
01:42:02.391 --> 01:42:04.457
Secondary protocol.

2323
01:42:10.399 --> 01:42:13.499
But they haven't drilled
the damn hole yet!

2324
01:42:17.281 --> 01:42:19.532
The president's advisors feel
that the drilling isn't working.

2325
01:42:19.533 --> 01:42:21.492
And we've lost radio contact,
maybe for good.

2326
01:42:21.493 --> 01:42:22.618
We've only got a few minutes left of

2327
01:42:22.619 --> 01:42:24.829
guaranteed ability to
remote detonate that nuke.

2328
01:42:24.830 --> 01:42:27.415
If we don't do it now we could lose
control, and we may never get it back.

2329
01:42:27.416 --> 01:42:28.887
Well, you tell
the president that

2330
01:42:28.915 --> 01:42:30.710
he better fire his
so-called advisors.

2331
01:42:30.711 --> 01:42:32.295
If you detonate that nuke on the surface,

2332
01:42:32.296 --> 01:42:34.088
we waste a perfectly good bomb,

2333
01:42:34.089 --> 01:42:36.007
and we have one chance
to save this planet!

2334
01:42:36.008 --> 01:42:37.778
[Beeping]

2335
01:42:46.977 --> 01:42:48.797
I need that radio.

2336
01:42:49.021 --> 01:42:51.314
Gruber, give me
everything you got now!

2337
01:42:51.315 --> 01:42:52.543
[Gruber] Roger that.

2338
01:42:55.694 --> 01:42:57.487
Yes, Mr. President,
I understand that completely,

2339
01:42:57.488 --> 01:42:59.614
but my point is very, very simple.

2340
01:42:59.615 --> 01:43:00.985
And I think you need
to trust me on this

2341
01:43:01.013 --> 01:43:02.241
because I know
something about it.

2342
01:43:02.242 --> 01:43:03.655
I guarantee you,

2343
01:43:03.683 --> 01:43:06.523
if you do this,
you kill us all.

2344
01:43:09.249 --> 01:43:10.921
Yes, sir.

2345
01:43:11.168 --> 01:43:14.415
General, he wants you.

2346
01:43:15.798 --> 01:43:18.454
This is Kimsey. Yes, sir.

2347
01:43:19.176 --> 01:43:20.898
I understand.

2348
01:43:23.555 --> 01:43:27.308
The orders are to remote detonate
in 30 seconds.

2349
01:43:27.309 --> 01:43:29.695
You have not told them yet!

2350
01:43:29.723 --> 01:43:32.109
That is my father up there!

2351
01:43:32.523 --> 01:43:34.626
This is one order
you shouldn't follow,

2352
01:43:34.654 --> 01:43:35.942
and you fucking know it!

2353
01:43:35.943 --> 01:43:38.255
Let her go. Let her go!

2354
01:43:40.864 --> 01:43:42.635
Your key, sir.

2355
01:43:44.827 --> 01:43:46.094
(CONSOLES BEEPING)

2356
01:43:47.496 --> 01:43:49.513
God be with them.

2357
01:43:50.332 --> 01:43:52.208
Slow it down.

2358
01:43:52.209 --> 01:43:53.232
(BEEPING)

2359
01:43:54.878 --> 01:43:55.898
(TIMER BEEPING)

2360
01:43:58.549 --> 01:43:59.574
Harry.

2361
01:44:00.551 --> 01:44:02.579
The clock on that nine-foot

2362
01:44:02.607 --> 01:44:04.634
nuclear weapon is ticking.

2363
01:44:05.556 --> 01:44:06.969
Oh, my God!

2364
01:44:06.997 --> 01:44:09.340
Sharp! Get back here now!

2365
01:44:10.394 --> 01:44:12.562
What?
Get the shuttle ready to evac now!

2366
01:44:12.563 --> 01:44:13.896
It just came on all by itself.

2367
01:44:13.897 --> 01:44:15.523
- What the hell's happening?
- Secondary protocol.

2368
01:44:15.524 --> 01:44:17.525
- What's that? What?
- Secondary protocol.

2369
01:44:17.526 --> 01:44:19.152
- What does that mean?
- What the hell's secondary protocol?

2370
01:44:19.153 --> 01:44:20.444
They're detonating this thing from Earth.

2371
01:44:20.445 --> 01:44:21.612
What do you mean, detonating?

2372
01:44:21.613 --> 01:44:22.864
- We haven't even drilled the hole yet!
- We'll drop it in the hole.

2373
01:44:22.865 --> 01:44:24.115
- What're you talkin' about?
- The hole? Whoa, whoa!

2374
01:44:24.116 --> 01:44:25.283
Get your helmets on now!

2375
01:44:25.284 --> 01:44:26.945
Oh, no, no. How...
How you turn it off?

2376
01:44:26.973 --> 01:44:28.369
I got two men
out on that rock!

2377
01:44:28.370 --> 01:44:30.705
I got a man out there, too.
We gotta evac now.

2378
01:44:30.706 --> 01:44:32.748
Max, Rockhound,
get back to the shuttle, double-time!

2379
01:44:32.749 --> 01:44:34.236
ROCKHOUND: <i>They
could be on their way here.</i>

2380
01:44:34.264 --> 01:44:35.751
MAX: <i>They're not
on their way here.</i>

2381
01:44:35.752 --> 01:44:37.409
<i>They would've
talked to us by now.</i>

2382
01:44:37.437 --> 01:44:38.588
We would've seen them.

2383
01:44:38.589 --> 01:44:41.883
- Watts, air lock the cockpit now!
- I copy you.

2384
01:44:41.884 --> 01:44:43.801
- Max, Rockhound!
- Hey, wait a minute!

2385
01:44:43.802 --> 01:44:45.261
How do you turn
this thing off?

2386
01:44:45.262 --> 01:44:46.354
(RADIO STATIC HISSING)

2387
01:44:46.555 --> 01:44:48.681
- <i>Harry, do you copy?</i>
- <i>Something's wrong.</i>

2388
01:44:48.682 --> 01:44:50.128
<i>Yeah, it's all wrong, man.</i>

2389
01:44:50.156 --> 01:44:51.601
<i>We shouldn't
even be up here.</i>

2390
01:44:51.602 --> 01:44:53.285
<i>I know. Let's go
back to the ship!</i>

2391
01:44:54.771 --> 01:44:56.564
I'm not leavin' without my men, Sharp.

2392
01:44:56.565 --> 01:44:57.969
We've got two
and a half minutes

2393
01:44:57.997 --> 01:44:59.400
to drop it and
get off this rock.

2394
01:44:59.401 --> 01:45:01.042
If they're not back
by the time we finish,

2395
01:45:01.070 --> 01:45:01.944
we leave without 'em.

2396
01:45:01.945 --> 01:45:02.932
Okay, let's simplify this.

2397
01:45:02.960 --> 01:45:04.447
Let's just turn the
bomb off right now.

2398
01:45:04.448 --> 01:45:05.751
If we don't put
this bomb down

2399
01:45:05.779 --> 01:45:07.491
in a hole 800 feet
onto a fault line,

2400
01:45:07.492 --> 01:45:09.702
all you're gonna have is
a real expensive fireworks show.

2401
01:45:09.703 --> 01:45:10.955
This is turnin' into a

2402
01:45:10.983 --> 01:45:12.580
surrealistic
nightmare here.

2403
01:45:12.581 --> 01:45:14.957
Watsler, are you listening? It's Truman.

2404
01:45:14.958 --> 01:45:16.808
Okay, listen
to me carefully.

2405
01:45:16.836 --> 01:45:19.484
I want you to kill it.
Kill the uplink.

2406
01:45:30.307 --> 01:45:32.892
Give us the time, Sharp.
Shut this bomb down now!

2407
01:45:32.893 --> 01:45:34.560
- It's not my call.
- Then whose call is it?

2408
01:45:34.561 --> 01:45:36.646
An order to detonate can
only come from the president.

2409
01:45:36.647 --> 01:45:38.272
- The president's not here!
- Let's just turn it off now.

2410
01:45:38.273 --> 01:45:39.482
You've gotta give us more time!

2411
01:45:39.483 --> 01:45:40.816
I'm telling you to
shut this bomb down now!

2412
01:45:40.817 --> 01:45:42.485
And I'm telling you it's not my call!

2413
01:45:42.486 --> 01:45:44.487
Well, guess what.
I just made the call for you.

2414
01:45:44.488 --> 01:45:45.913
Harry!

2415
01:45:47.824 --> 01:45:50.993
Don't. You could set it off.

2416
01:45:50.994 --> 01:45:52.038
Oh, man.

2417
01:45:52.066 --> 01:45:55.225
What're you doin'
with a gun in space?

2418
01:45:57.668 --> 01:45:58.807
Come on, come on.

2419
01:45:58.835 --> 01:46:01.128
We gotta stop that
bomb right now.

2420
01:46:01.129 --> 01:46:02.654
Kill the uplink.

2421
01:46:02.798 --> 01:46:04.715
This thing is gonna blow.

2422
01:46:04.716 --> 01:46:07.760
- We gotta get it off the ship.
- Easy.

2423
01:46:07.761 --> 01:46:09.178
Stand down, Sergeant.

2424
01:46:09.179 --> 01:46:10.454
Shut this bomb down

2425
01:46:10.482 --> 01:46:13.182
and let us finish
our job the right way.

2426
01:46:13.183 --> 01:46:15.893
I'm under orders to protect
a surface detonation.

2427
01:46:15.894 --> 01:46:18.271
I'm gonna give you three seconds
to shut this bomb down,

2428
01:46:18.272 --> 01:46:20.436
and then I'm gonna make you shoot me.

2429
01:46:21.149 --> 01:46:23.904
Hurry, Watsler. For Christ's sake, hurry.

2430
01:46:26.029 --> 01:46:27.030
(POWERING DOWN)

2431
01:46:27.531 --> 01:46:29.745
What happened?

2432
01:46:30.575 --> 01:46:31.602
(GROANS)

2433
01:46:32.619 --> 01:46:33.703
(GRUNTING)

2434
01:46:33.704 --> 01:46:35.781
Sir, the override...

2435
01:46:35.809 --> 01:46:37.886
It's been overridden.

2436
01:46:38.208 --> 01:46:39.375
I bought us a couple of minutes,

2437
01:46:39.376 --> 01:46:41.178
so get that radio workin', okay?

2438
01:46:41.206 --> 01:46:41.930
Hurry, hurry!

2439
01:46:42.170 --> 01:46:43.341
(GRUNTING)

2440
01:46:44.047 --> 01:46:45.951
Bring me all the
way up here just to

2441
01:46:45.979 --> 01:46:47.883
blow me and my
friends up? Is that it?

2442
01:46:47.884 --> 01:46:49.462
(GASPING) Listen...

2443
01:46:49.491 --> 01:46:50.501
Shut up!

2444
01:46:50.720 --> 01:46:51.829
HARRY: Shut up, Colonel.

2445
01:46:51.858 --> 01:46:53.001
I'm talking now.

2446
01:46:54.725 --> 01:46:56.809
SHARP: It could start again.
It might've been a warning.

2447
01:46:56.810 --> 01:46:57.911
(CONTINUES GASPING)

2448
01:46:58.895 --> 01:46:59.937
Uh-oh.

2449
01:46:59.938 --> 01:47:02.281
That's why you are gonna
dismantle this bomb.

2450
01:47:02.441 --> 01:47:04.789
<i>All right. What'd we miss?</i>

2451
01:47:09.531 --> 01:47:12.926
- Do it again.
- Go.

2452
01:47:15.871 --> 01:47:18.133
Keep tryin'.

2453
01:47:19.082 --> 01:47:21.693
Sir, I need you to
cease and desist.

2454
01:47:21.721 --> 01:47:23.882
I need your terminal, now.

2455
01:47:27.049 --> 01:47:28.551
They're reactivating
the bomb.

2456
01:47:28.579 --> 01:47:29.925
Comin' back on-line, sir.

2457
01:47:29.926 --> 01:47:32.793
- (DETONATOR BEEPING)
- Oh, geez. Here we go again.

2458
01:47:33.305 --> 01:47:34.436
What're you doin' up here?

2459
01:47:34.750 --> 01:47:36.432
And why did you even
bother to make the trip?

2460
01:47:36.433 --> 01:47:39.101
To do the right thing,
to see that it's done.

2461
01:47:39.768 --> 01:47:41.104
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2462
01:47:42.397 --> 01:47:43.495
(GASPING)

2463
01:47:47.089 --> 01:47:49.018
For God's sakes,
think about what you're doin'.

2464
01:47:50.044 --> 01:47:52.698
Why are you listenin' to someone
that's 100,000 miles away?

2465
01:47:53.617 --> 01:47:54.706
We're here.

2466
01:47:55.159 --> 01:47:56.784
Nobody down
there can help us.

2467
01:47:57.287 --> 01:47:58.808
So if we don't
get this job done,

2468
01:47:59.964 --> 01:48:01.165
then everybody's gone.

2469
01:48:01.166 --> 01:48:02.175
One minute.

2470
01:48:03.794 --> 01:48:06.003
I've been drillin' holes
in the earth for 30 years.

2471
01:48:06.588 --> 01:48:09.097
And I have never,
never missed

2472
01:48:09.136 --> 01:48:10.604
a depth that I
have aimed for.

2473
01:48:11.426 --> 01:48:13.167
And by God, I
am not gonna miss

2474
01:48:13.212 --> 01:48:14.970
this one. I will
make 800 feet.

2475
01:48:14.971 --> 01:48:16.143
Forty-two seconds.

2476
01:48:18.078 --> 01:48:20.347
But I can't do it alone, Colonel.
I need your help.

2477
01:48:21.144 --> 01:48:23.331
You swear on your daughter's life,

2478
01:48:23.360 --> 01:48:24.479
on my family's,

2479
01:48:24.731 --> 01:48:26.487
that you can hit that mark?

2480
01:48:27.484 --> 01:48:29.062
I will make 800 feet.

2481
01:48:29.690 --> 01:48:31.214
I swear to God, I will.

2482
01:48:31.863 --> 01:48:33.401
Then let's turn this bomb off.

2483
01:48:36.109 --> 01:48:37.129
(BEEPING)

2484
01:48:37.383 --> 01:48:38.643
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

2485
01:48:43.750 --> 01:48:44.960
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

2486
01:48:46.253 --> 01:48:47.920
Steady. Take it back.

2487
01:48:47.921 --> 01:48:49.922
That's what you'll have to do.
Get 'em off backwards.

2488
01:48:49.923 --> 01:48:51.507
Rainbow track? Under...

2489
01:48:51.508 --> 01:48:53.134
- Under one? Under... Okay.
- All of 'em. All of 'em.

2490
01:48:53.135 --> 01:48:54.921
Okay. Are we free of static?

2491
01:48:54.949 --> 01:48:56.679
Oh, do a good job. Do a good job.

2492
01:48:56.680 --> 01:48:59.056
- Steady. Steady.
- Good job. All right. All right.

2493
01:48:59.057 --> 01:49:01.510
Go! Go! Go! Red wire "A."

2494
01:49:01.538 --> 01:49:02.852
Ready? And...

2495
01:49:02.853 --> 01:49:04.728
Now. Come on! Come on!
Come on! Come on!

2496
01:49:04.729 --> 01:49:06.063
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

2497
01:49:06.064 --> 01:49:07.231
Negative "B."

2498
01:49:07.232 --> 01:49:09.216
- Ready, and now.
- Do a good job. Do a good job.

2499
01:49:10.193 --> 01:49:11.694
Track flipped. Hot's in.

2500
01:49:11.695 --> 01:49:13.112
- It better be. Go.
- Red or blue?

2501
01:49:13.159 --> 01:49:14.292
(CONTINUES BEEPING)

2502
01:49:16.199 --> 01:49:17.019
Re...

2503
01:49:19.995 --> 01:49:21.078
(WHIMPERING)

2504
01:49:21.323 --> 01:49:22.338
(CONTINUES BEEPING)

2505
01:49:22.656 --> 01:49:23.659
Blue.

2506
01:49:24.583 --> 01:49:25.877
(STOPS BEEPING)

2507
01:49:27.085 --> 01:49:28.088
Good job!

2508
01:49:28.378 --> 01:49:30.057
(ALL PANTING DEEPLY)

2509
01:49:32.557 --> 01:49:33.604
(EXHALES)

2510
01:49:33.633 --> 01:49:36.026
Oh, God, it sucks up here.

2511
01:49:36.887 --> 01:49:39.432
Sir, the clock has stopped
at three seconds.

2512
01:49:39.681 --> 01:49:40.465
What?

2513
01:49:41.600 --> 01:49:43.137
Have we lost complete radio contact?

2514
01:49:43.852 --> 01:49:45.060
I got some magic happening.

2515
01:49:45.061 --> 01:49:46.479
We're bouncing off Russian
and French satellites.

2516
01:49:46.480 --> 01:49:48.332
- It may have a faint signal.
- HARRY: <i>Houston?</i>

2517
01:49:49.139 --> 01:49:50.582
<i>Houston, do you copy?</i>

2518
01:49:52.235 --> 01:49:54.570
Go ahead, Freedom.

2519
01:49:54.571 --> 01:49:56.047
Houston, you have
a problem.

2520
01:49:57.407 --> 01:49:59.875
See, I promised my little
girl that I'd be comin' home.

2521
01:50:01.313 --> 01:50:03.578
Now, I don't know what you people
are doin' down there,

2522
01:50:04.206 --> 01:50:05.789
but we got a hole
to dig up there.

2523
01:50:06.203 --> 01:50:07.289
(ALL CHEERING)

2524
01:50:07.626 --> 01:50:09.586
Go, go, go, go! Come on.
We got work to do.

2525
01:50:09.920 --> 01:50:11.657
<i>Okay, guys. All go, no quit.</i>

2526
01:50:11.685 --> 01:50:13.422
<i>How ya doin' down there? Good?</i>

2527
01:50:13.423 --> 01:50:16.099
<i>Okay, got the tranny.
We're back in business.</i>

2528
01:50:16.426 --> 01:50:18.302
<i>Hey, you guys
should take a break</i>

2529
01:50:18.331 --> 01:50:19.748
<i>and come up and see this.</i>

2530
01:50:21.677 --> 01:50:24.216
<i>Wow. Got a great view
of the Earth from here.</i>

2531
01:50:24.434 --> 01:50:26.519
<i>Too bad we'll never
set foot on her again.</i>

2532
01:50:26.613 --> 01:50:28.081
A.J: <i>Lev, do you
see anything?</i>

2533
01:50:28.110 --> 01:50:29.063
LEV: <i>No.</i>

2534
01:50:29.064 --> 01:50:32.441
Well, keep goin'. I'm not givin' up.

2535
01:50:32.442 --> 01:50:34.443
Hold up here, Bear.

2536
01:50:34.444 --> 01:50:36.612
- LEV: Oh, boy.
- A.J.: This is great.

2537
01:50:36.613 --> 01:50:39.615
We just happen to run into
the Grand Canyon on the asteroid?

2538
01:50:39.616 --> 01:50:42.910
I told you, you took a wrong way,
a wrong road.

2539
01:50:42.911 --> 01:50:44.371
A.J.: <i>What... What road?</i>

2540
01:50:44.399 --> 01:50:46.330
<i>Do you see any
roads around here?</i>

2541
01:50:46.331 --> 01:50:47.482
LEV: You know what?

2542
01:50:47.510 --> 01:50:50.501
<i>I do not have much
pleasure being near God's ear.</i>

2543
01:50:50.502 --> 01:50:53.128
<i>But you think this is
looking good, or what?</i>

2544
01:50:53.129 --> 01:50:55.515
<i>Lev, why don't you
just do humanity</i>

2545
01:50:55.543 --> 01:50:57.394
<i>a favor and just
shut the hell up?</i>

2546
01:51:02.681 --> 01:51:04.598
<i>Have you ever heard of Evel Knievel?</i>

2547
01:51:04.599 --> 01:51:07.404
<i>No, I never saw Star Wars.</i>

2548
01:51:12.983 --> 01:51:15.526
All right. Doin' a good job.

2549
01:51:15.527 --> 01:51:18.320
- Give me a depth reading, Max.
- We're 150 feet, Harry.

2550
01:51:18.321 --> 01:51:22.408
[Humming William Tell Overture]

2551
01:51:22.409 --> 01:51:23.659
Yee-ha!

2552
01:51:23.660 --> 01:51:25.188
Ride 'em, cowboy!

2553
01:51:25.216 --> 01:51:27.288
Yippee-kai-yo, kai-yay!

2554
01:51:27.289 --> 01:51:28.367
Get off...

2555
01:51:29.273 --> 01:51:30.283
the nuclear...

2556
01:51:30.749 --> 01:51:31.764
warhead.

2557
01:51:31.793 --> 01:51:33.430
I was doin' that
guy from that movie,

2558
01:51:33.458 --> 01:51:34.545
you know, Slim Pickens,

2559
01:51:34.546 --> 01:51:36.067
where he rides
it all the way in,

2560
01:51:36.095 --> 01:51:37.089
the nuclear warhead.

2561
01:51:37.090 --> 01:51:38.075
Now.

2562
01:51:38.104 --> 01:51:39.432
Oh, you didn't
see that one, huh?

2563
01:51:40.051 --> 01:51:43.012
We got 700 feet of
hole to dig, Rockhound.

2564
01:51:43.013 --> 01:51:45.432
All right. Just...
Just wanted to feel

2565
01:51:45.460 --> 01:51:47.813
the power between
my legs, brother.

2566
01:51:48.727 --> 01:51:50.769
Hey, Sharp.

2567
01:51:50.770 --> 01:51:52.941
(CHATTING) No
nukes! No nukes!

2568
01:51:53.732 --> 01:51:55.590
You got any more bullets
in that gun, Sharp?

2569
01:51:56.067 --> 01:51:57.263
A.J.: <i>What did Watts tell you, Bear?</i>

2570
01:51:57.291 --> 01:51:58.319
<i>If she kicked you in the balls,</i>

2571
01:51:58.320 --> 01:51:59.528
- <i>you'd keep floating.</i>
- Yeah.

2572
01:51:59.529 --> 01:52:00.696
(ENGINE ROARING)

2573
01:52:02.365 --> 01:52:03.846
A.J.: We turn
the thrusters off,

2574
01:52:03.874 --> 01:52:04.825
we jump this thing,

2575
01:52:04.826 --> 01:52:06.843
we float right over it.

2576
01:52:07.120 --> 01:52:09.204
Go over it again, Lev.

2577
01:52:09.205 --> 01:52:11.138
Throw the jet thrusters off

2578
01:52:11.166 --> 01:52:12.666
exactly when we jump.

2579
01:52:12.667 --> 01:52:14.251
- Okay.
- And then we're gonna put them on,

2580
01:52:14.252 --> 01:52:16.378
and we gonna go down nice and slow.

2581
01:52:16.379 --> 01:52:20.049
- That's it. That's it, baby. That's it.
- Is this gonna work?

2582
01:52:20.050 --> 01:52:21.125
I don't know.

2583
01:52:21.518 --> 01:52:24.073
Lev, you know
what, just lie to me.

2584
01:52:24.220 --> 01:52:25.501
Let's say 50-50

2585
01:52:25.574 --> 01:52:27.751
No. More like, uh...

2586
01:52:28.224 --> 01:52:31.352
Like 70-30 or 80-20.
But you know what?

2587
01:52:31.353 --> 01:52:33.978
If it works, the two of you
gonna be heroes,

2588
01:52:34.532 --> 01:52:35.626
just like me.

2589
01:52:35.899 --> 01:52:36.946
Screw it.

2590
01:52:36.975 --> 01:52:38.408
We're jumpin' over this canyon.

2591
01:52:42.906 --> 01:52:45.696
Just for the record,
this is a very bad idea!

2592
01:52:49.371 --> 01:52:50.537
Wait for the edge.

2593
01:52:50.538 --> 01:52:53.205
- Don't hit it till we get there.
- I'm waiting.

2594
01:52:53.583 --> 01:52:55.176
- LEV: Three.
- (A.J. CHATTERING)

2595
01:52:56.920 --> 01:52:58.068
LEV: Two.

2596
01:52:58.451 --> 01:52:59.421
One!

2597
01:52:59.562 --> 01:53:00.608
(SCREAMING)

2598
01:53:09.224 --> 01:53:12.601
- Yes! It's working!
- It's working!

2599
01:53:12.602 --> 01:53:13.852
LEV: Oh, my God!

2600
01:53:14.011 --> 01:53:15.159
(ALL SHOUTING EXCITEDLY)

2601
01:53:15.188 --> 01:53:16.445
I'm a genius!

2602
01:53:16.695 --> 01:53:17.969
Wait a minute.

2603
01:53:18.952 --> 01:53:20.328
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa!

2604
01:53:20.568 --> 01:53:22.736
- We got some rocks!
- Go left! Go left!

2605
01:53:22.737 --> 01:53:24.875
Lev, Lev, I can't do anything!

2606
01:53:25.407 --> 01:53:26.422
(ALL SCREAMING)

2607
01:53:26.881 --> 01:53:28.039
(CRASHING)

2608
01:53:35.083 --> 01:53:35.934
Oh, okay, okay,

2609
01:53:35.962 --> 01:53:37.793
we're floating
into outer space.

2610
01:53:37.794 --> 01:53:39.294
- Check main switch.
- Uh, this could be

2611
01:53:39.295 --> 01:53:41.422
a little bit of a problem.

2612
01:53:41.423 --> 01:53:43.674
- Thrusters on... Now!
- All right, turn 'em on.

2613
01:53:43.675 --> 01:53:44.807
(ENGINES POWERING DOWN)

2614
01:53:46.761 --> 01:53:48.512
- What's wrong?
- I... I don't know.

2615
01:53:48.513 --> 01:53:50.395
The... The thrusters not working.

2616
01:53:50.661 --> 01:53:52.099
I hate this machine!

2617
01:53:52.100 --> 01:53:53.308
I thought you had this planned!

2618
01:53:53.309 --> 01:53:55.060
- What're we supposed to do?
- Be quiet! I must think!

2619
01:53:55.061 --> 01:53:57.813
- I'm stepping outside.
- You're... You're going outside?

2620
01:53:57.814 --> 01:54:01.191
I am the only
certified astronaut,

2621
01:54:01.220 --> 01:54:03.407
and I'm saving
your American ass!

2622
01:54:04.918 --> 01:54:05.942
(LEV GRUNTS)

2623
01:54:07.532 --> 01:54:08.814
Yes. You'll listen to him.

2624
01:54:08.843 --> 01:54:09.893
Right.

2625
01:54:15.165 --> 01:54:17.090
A.J.: <i>Hurry up, Lev,
because we're</i>

2626
01:54:17.118 --> 01:54:19.042
<i>about a mile
off the asteroid!</i>

2627
01:54:19.043 --> 01:54:20.226
<i>Just a second.</i>

2628
01:54:20.254 --> 01:54:21.980
<i>The fuel line is iced up.</i>

2629
01:54:22.464 --> 01:54:24.514
<i>I think maybe workin' now.</i>

2630
01:54:24.542 --> 01:54:26.592
No, Lev, it's not working!

2631
01:54:26.593 --> 01:54:29.374
<i>I'm sorry, A.J., I
was way off the odds.</i>

2632
01:54:29.596 --> 01:54:31.096
BEAR: <i>We're gettin' higher, man.</i>

2633
01:54:31.097 --> 01:54:32.553
<i>Look out! The rocks!</i>

2634
01:54:32.662 --> 01:54:34.155
<i>Rocks are coming!</i>

2635
01:54:38.439 --> 01:54:39.604
(LEV GRUNTING)

2636
01:54:40.753 --> 01:54:41.854
Hold on!

2637
01:54:42.459 --> 01:54:43.685
(LEV SCREAMING)

2638
01:54:46.696 --> 01:54:48.406
<i>Pull the thrusters!</i>

2639
01:54:48.435 --> 01:54:49.547
Lev, look out!

2640
01:54:51.409 --> 01:54:52.502
(ALL SCREAMING)

2641
01:54:56.456 --> 01:54:58.373
- We lost Lev.
- LEV: <i>A.J.!</i>

2642
01:54:58.374 --> 01:54:59.666
(GRUNTING)

2643
01:54:59.667 --> 01:55:02.044
<i>A.J., the thrusters!</i>

2644
01:55:02.045 --> 01:55:03.190
(YELLING)

2645
01:55:06.174 --> 01:55:07.517
Let's get Lev back!

2646
01:55:09.454 --> 01:55:10.791
(LEV CONTINUES SCREAMING)

2647
01:55:11.554 --> 01:55:12.814
(GASPING)

2648
01:55:16.392 --> 01:55:18.799
Lev, hold on!
We're comin' in!

2649
01:55:20.271 --> 01:55:21.396
(GRUNTING)

2650
01:55:26.814 --> 01:55:27.856
(GROANING)

2651
01:55:30.448 --> 01:55:32.567
(BOTH PANTING)

2652
01:55:33.375 --> 01:55:34.380
(GRUNTS)

2653
01:55:35.583 --> 01:55:36.711
Thank You, Jesus.

2654
01:55:36.739 --> 01:55:37.704
Thank You, Lord.

2655
01:55:37.705 --> 01:55:39.458
Thank You. Thank You,
thank You, thank You, thank You.

2656
01:55:40.041 --> 01:55:41.153
(A.J. GRUNTS)

2657
01:55:42.067 --> 01:55:43.072
<i>Lev!</i>

2658
01:55:43.692 --> 01:55:46.536
<i>Now I'm really
a Russian hero!</i>

2659
01:55:47.278 --> 01:55:48.298
<i>I told you!</i>

2660
01:55:48.299 --> 01:55:50.759
- <i>I know!</i>
- <i>I knew this would work!</i>

2661
01:55:50.760 --> 01:55:53.178
- <i>Good odds, you know?</i>
- <i>Come on, Lev.</i>

2662
01:55:53.179 --> 01:55:54.295
<i>Get in here.
We gotta go.</i>

2663
01:55:54.323 --> 01:55:55.427
(YELLING)

2664
01:55:56.307 --> 01:55:57.307
(RUMBLING)

2665
01:55:59.477 --> 01:56:01.619
<i>Rockhound, keep
on that transmission.</i>

2666
01:56:01.813 --> 01:56:03.449
<i>Tranny looks good, Harry.</i>

2667
01:56:03.478 --> 01:56:04.940
<i>All right. Take it outta there.</i>

2668
01:56:04.941 --> 01:56:06.062
<i>Lock it down, Chick.</i>

2669
01:56:08.845 --> 01:56:09.875
<i>Nice.</i>

2670
01:56:11.239 --> 01:56:13.234
<i>How come we didn't get
any training on this thing?</i>

2671
01:56:14.534 --> 01:56:16.104
<i>Whoa. Very cool.</i>

2672
01:56:16.284 --> 01:56:18.245
<i>I could take out
this asteroid single-handedly.</i>

2673
01:56:18.246 --> 01:56:19.329
(MACHINE WHIRRING)

2674
01:56:19.330 --> 01:56:21.456
<i>Okay, boys, give it a rest.
I'll take it from here.</i>

2675
01:56:21.457 --> 01:56:22.464
(MACHINE GUN FIRING)

2676
01:56:22.667 --> 01:56:23.667
<i>Whoa!</i>

2677
01:56:24.544 --> 01:56:26.336
<i>- What the hell is that?
- It's Rockhound.</i>

2678
01:56:26.337 --> 01:56:27.317
<i>Whoa!</i>

2679
01:56:27.629 --> 01:56:29.606
<i>This is so
much fun, it's freaky.</i>

2680
01:56:29.634 --> 01:56:30.790
(FIRING CONTINUES)

2681
01:56:31.134 --> 01:56:32.175
<i>Rockhound!</i>

2682
01:56:32.176 --> 01:56:33.406
<i>Whoo!</i>

2683
01:56:33.469 --> 01:56:35.453
<i>Whoa, watch your heads. Sorry, Harry.</i>

2684
01:56:38.349 --> 01:56:40.809
<i>- Outta my way, boys!
- Rockhound!</i>

2685
01:56:40.810 --> 01:56:42.836
<i>Meet your maker, asteroid!</i>

2686
01:56:43.630 --> 01:56:44.633
(HARRY GRUNTS)

2687
01:56:48.151 --> 01:56:49.985
<i>What the hell's the matter with you,
Rockhound?</i>

2688
01:56:49.986 --> 01:56:51.987
<i>- Goddamn!
- This is insane.</i>

2689
01:56:51.988 --> 01:56:53.614
<i>- Have you lost your mind?
- No.</i>

2690
01:56:53.615 --> 01:56:55.083
<i>He's got space dementia.</i>

2691
01:56:55.615 --> 01:56:57.474
<i>Harry, you want to watch your man.</i>

2692
01:57:00.233 --> 01:57:01.373
<i>Max.</i>

2693
01:57:02.128 --> 01:57:03.984
<i>Downshift
and put it in reverse.</i>

2694
01:57:04.013 --> 01:57:05.088
<i>We gotta get that pipe outta there.</i>

2695
01:57:05.126 --> 01:57:06.376
MAX: Uh-oh.

2696
01:57:06.377 --> 01:57:07.502
(GRUNTS)

2697
01:57:07.580 --> 01:57:08.832
(RUMBLING LOUDLY)

2698
01:57:09.756 --> 01:57:12.174
- What's happening?
- <i>The ground's cracking!</i>

2699
01:57:12.175 --> 01:57:13.552
<i>Earthquake!</i>

2700
01:57:21.559 --> 01:57:22.764
HARRY:  <i>Quick, shut it off!</i>

2701
01:57:24.854 --> 01:57:26.571
<i>Shut it off! Shut it off now!</i>

2702
01:57:26.599 --> 01:57:28.315
<i>We're gonna have a blowout!</i>

2703
01:57:28.316 --> 01:57:31.026
<i>- We hit a gas pocket!
- We got pressure out the ass!</i>

2704
01:57:31.027 --> 01:57:32.095
(GRUNTING)

2705
01:57:33.196 --> 01:57:34.913
<i>Max, get your helmet on!</i>

2706
01:57:34.941 --> 01:57:36.657
<i>Max, it's gonna blow!</i>

2707
01:57:36.658 --> 01:57:38.737
(SCREAMS) Jesus, I'm cooking!

2708
01:57:38.766 --> 01:57:40.035
<i>Max, get outta there!</i>

2709
01:57:40.036 --> 01:57:41.309
MAX: This is it!

2710
01:57:42.983 --> 01:57:44.145
Harry!

2711
01:57:46.876 --> 01:57:47.887
I'm bailing!

2712
01:57:52.006 --> 01:57:53.131
(SCREAMING) <i>Max!</i>

2713
01:57:56.219 --> 01:57:57.302
<i>Good-bye, Max.</i>

2714
01:57:57.365 --> 01:57:58.466
(SCREAMING) <i>Max!</i>

2715
01:57:59.513 --> 01:58:00.646
<i>Take care, buddy.</i>

2716
01:58:00.848 --> 01:58:03.016
- Armadillo's off the scope.
- I think we've had a blowout.

2717
01:58:03.017 --> 01:58:04.685
No sign of the Armadillo.

2718
01:58:04.920 --> 01:58:06.068
(ALL CLAMORING)

2719
01:58:08.151 --> 01:58:09.654
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

2720
01:58:36.175 --> 01:58:37.565
Get a hold of Truman.

2721
01:58:39.679 --> 01:58:41.589
Prepare the world for bad news.

2722
01:58:42.741 --> 01:58:43.940
(SIRENS WAILING)

2723
01:58:49.188 --> 01:58:51.648
NEWSCASTER #1: <i>We're getting
sketchy information that the mission</i>

2724
01:58:51.649 --> 01:58:54.109
<i>has suffered massive failure.</i>

2725
01:58:54.110 --> 01:58:56.778
<i>And what we're trying to do right now
is to confirm that</i>

2726
01:58:56.779 --> 01:58:58.363
<i>and find out exactly what that means.</i>

2727
01:58:58.364 --> 01:59:01.616
<i>Repeat. We're getting leaks
from several NASA officials,</i>

2728
01:59:01.617 --> 01:59:03.452
<i>some rushing home
to be with their families,</i>

2729
01:59:03.453 --> 01:59:06.851
<i>that the drilling was unsuccessful.</i>

2730
01:59:08.291 --> 01:59:09.533
(CHANTING)

2731
01:59:11.669 --> 01:59:13.114
(NEWCASTER SPEAKING FRENCH)

2732
01:59:15.965 --> 01:59:18.480
NEWCASTER #2: <i>This could
very well be our final hour.</i>

2733
01:59:18.926 --> 01:59:20.199
(NEWCASTER SPEAKS
IN OTHER LANGUAGE)

2734
01:59:22.346 --> 01:59:24.431
NEWCASTER #3: <i>We're
gonna go off the air now.</i>

2735
01:59:24.432 --> 01:59:27.138
<i>Good luck and God bless.</i>

2736
01:59:30.980 --> 01:59:32.898
- MAN #1: We've got incoming.
- MAN #2: I got tracks.

2737
01:59:32.899 --> 01:59:35.609
NORAD's tracking four small
incoming over Europe.

2738
01:59:35.610 --> 01:59:37.766
I think one's about to hit near Paris.

2739
01:59:40.073 --> 01:59:41.307
(ASTEROID ROARING)

2740
01:59:44.535 --> 01:59:45.831
(ALL CLAMORING)

2741
01:59:47.296 --> 01:59:48.557
(ROARING CONTINUES)

2742
01:59:52.522 --> 01:59:53.924
(EXPLODING)

2743
01:59:55.694 --> 01:59:57.092
(CRUMPLING EXPLOSIONS)

2744
02:00:01.094 --> 02:00:02.304
(ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY)

2745
02:00:03.346 --> 02:00:04.888
<i>Reports are coming in.</i>

2746
02:00:04.889 --> 02:00:07.516
MALE NEWCASTER #1: <i>Martial law
has been implemented in 42 countries.</i>

2747
02:00:07.517 --> 02:00:10.060
MALE NEWCASTER #2: <i>Once
the asteroid hits zero barrier,</i>

2748
02:00:10.061 --> 02:00:14.481
<i>it will take about three hours
and 57 minutes to impact Earth.</i>

2749
02:00:14.482 --> 02:00:15.896
(SIRENS WAILING)

2750
02:00:18.402 --> 02:00:20.894
Well, I guess we do it the
president's way. I'll order an evac.

2751
02:00:21.114 --> 02:00:22.447
You can remote detonate.

2752
02:00:22.448 --> 02:00:24.157
You still don't think this'll work, do you?

2753
02:00:24.158 --> 02:00:25.909
What I think is irrelevant.

2754
02:00:25.910 --> 02:00:27.050
KIMSEY: We need to do it now.

2755
02:00:27.079 --> 02:00:28.113
(SIGHS) Fine.

2756
02:00:29.080 --> 02:00:31.331
- Can they still take off?
- We hope so.

2757
02:00:31.332 --> 02:00:33.458
You are the one that
pulled them into this!

2758
02:00:33.459 --> 02:00:35.217
That is my family up there,

2759
02:00:35.245 --> 02:00:37.593
so I don't wanna
hear, "We hope so"!

2760
02:00:42.552 --> 02:00:43.854
ROCKHOUND: <i>Guess what, guys?</i>

2761
02:00:43.882 --> 02:00:46.346
<i>It's time to
embrace the horror.</i>

2762
02:00:46.347 --> 02:00:50.481
<i>Look. We got front-row tickets
to the end of the Earth.</i>

2763
02:00:50.893 --> 02:00:52.033
(RADIO STATIC CRACKLING)

2764
02:01:01.487 --> 02:01:02.939
(RUMBLING)

2765
02:01:11.956 --> 02:01:13.498
<i>Yeah!</i>

2766
02:01:13.499 --> 02:01:14.875
<i>Way to go, baby!</i>

2767
02:01:14.876 --> 02:01:16.449
<i>Harry!</i>

2768
02:01:19.046 --> 02:01:20.444
(ALL CHEERING)

2769
02:01:21.725 --> 02:01:22.733
<i>Yeah!</i>

2770
02:01:23.176 --> 02:01:25.552
<i>Yo, Harry! What's up, baby?</i>

2771
02:01:25.553 --> 02:01:27.268
<i>Sharp, get that bomb outta there!</i>

2772
02:01:27.296 --> 02:01:28.435
<i><i>We got a hole to make!</i>

2773
02:01:29.640 --> 02:01:31.600
SHARP: <i>Houston, you're
not gonna believe this,</i>

2774
02:01:31.601 --> 02:01:33.018
<i>but the other Armadillo has arrived.</i>

2775
02:01:33.019 --> 02:01:34.464
(ALL CHEERING HAPPILY)

2776
02:01:34.493 --> 02:01:36.342
All right, people, listen up.

2777
02:01:36.635 --> 02:01:38.162
Settle down and focus.

2778
02:01:38.191 --> 02:01:40.692
MAN #1: Mechanical, get on-line.
MAN #2: P.P.O., gimme a setup.

2779
02:01:40.693 --> 02:01:41.862
Your boyfriend's back.

2780
02:01:43.112 --> 02:01:44.237
BEAR: <i>Yo, Harry!</i>

2781
02:01:44.385 --> 02:01:45.886
(ALL SHOUTING EXCITEDLY)

2782
02:01:47.116 --> 02:01:48.972
<i>Hey, Harry. You miss me?</i>

2783
02:01:49.202 --> 02:01:51.933
<i>A.J., I got just
five words for ya.</i>

2784
02:01:52.705 --> 02:01:54.458
<i>Damn glad to see ya, boy!</i>

2785
02:01:54.947 --> 02:01:55.957
<i>That's six words.</i>

2786
02:01:55.958 --> 02:01:57.334
<i>Chick, walk 'em down.</i>

2787
02:01:57.335 --> 02:01:59.502
A.J.: So where's this hole
you need dug?

2788
02:01:59.503 --> 02:02:01.682
WATTS: <i>Houston,
drilling has recommenced.</i>

2789
02:02:02.293 --> 02:02:04.510
Do you think they can drill
250 feet in an hour?

2790
02:02:05.885 --> 02:02:06.885
They better.

2791
02:02:07.720 --> 02:02:09.182
<i>Bring that piece on in, Bear.</i>

2792
02:02:10.431 --> 02:02:11.431
<i>Tractor pull.</i>

2793
02:02:12.808 --> 02:02:14.338
<i>I'm comin' down!</i>

2794
02:02:14.657 --> 02:02:16.645
<i>We got 250 feet to go.</i>

2795
02:02:16.646 --> 02:02:19.368
<i>It's our last transmission,
last drill head.</i>

2796
02:02:19.732 --> 02:02:20.950
<i>Punch it through.</i>

2797
02:02:21.521 --> 02:02:23.357
<i>First gear. We got contact.</i>

2798
02:02:23.945 --> 02:02:25.403
<i>Come on down, A.J.</i>

2799
02:02:25.583 --> 02:02:26.584
(BEAR GRUNTING)

2800
02:02:27.573 --> 02:02:28.907
I got this, man. Let's go!

2801
02:02:28.908 --> 02:02:30.325
Lev, the right engine hub.

2802
02:02:30.660 --> 02:02:32.724
<i>Houston, I'm getting no response
from the preflight sequence.</i>

2803
02:02:32.995 --> 02:02:34.733
(MUFFLED) Come on, now.
This is not...

2804
02:02:34.761 --> 02:02:36.665
Hey... Hey, come here.

2805
02:02:36.666 --> 02:02:38.153
Can you get me outta here, please, Lev?

2806
02:02:38.181 --> 02:02:39.042
Thank you.

2807
02:02:39.043 --> 02:02:40.049
(GRUNTING)

2808
02:02:40.734 --> 02:02:42.484
Ow! Jesus!

2809
02:02:42.513 --> 02:02:43.964
- Hey!
- Wait. Uh, shh, shh.

2810
02:02:43.965 --> 02:02:45.173
- [Watts] Lev, the right engine...
- Okay.

2811
02:02:45.174 --> 02:02:46.703
Lemme outta here, will ya?

2812
02:02:47.233 --> 02:02:49.578
Tryin' to have some
fun before I die!

2813
02:02:49.855 --> 02:02:50.964
<i>How deep are we?</i>

2814
02:02:52.418 --> 02:02:53.535
<i>770.</i>

2815
02:02:56.077 --> 02:02:57.084
(GRUNTING)

2816
02:02:58.688 --> 02:03:00.897
- Whoa, they got problems.
- The gauges are spiking.

2817
02:03:00.898 --> 02:03:02.983
<i>Methane! Shut it down!
Back it down!</i>

2818
02:03:02.984 --> 02:03:05.110
<i>I can't pull back now.
The bit'll get lodged.</i>

2819
02:03:05.111 --> 02:03:06.312
<i>We don't have enough time!</i>

2820
02:03:07.196 --> 02:03:08.836
<i>Whoa, whoa, whoa!
It's gonna blow!</i>

2821
02:03:09.462 --> 02:03:10.949
<i>It's how we lost Max!</i>

2822
02:03:10.950 --> 02:03:13.243
<i>I know what I'm talkin' about.
We can punch through this.</i>

2823
02:03:13.244 --> 02:03:14.911
<i>We can knock
this outta the park.</i>

2824
02:03:14.912 --> 02:03:16.830
<i>This is our last
transmission, A.J.</i>

2825
02:03:16.831 --> 02:03:19.124
<i>Goddamn it, if you're
ever gonna trust me, ever,</i>

2826
02:03:19.125 --> 02:03:21.478
<i>once in your
life, trust me now!</i>

2827
02:03:22.086 --> 02:03:23.878
<i>Harry, it's gonna blow!</i>

2828
02:03:23.879 --> 02:03:25.371
<i>Harry, I know what I'm
doin'.</i>

2829
02:03:25.400 --> 02:03:26.643
<i>You just gotta trust me.</i>

2830
02:03:28.426 --> 02:03:29.455
<i>Make the call.</i>

2831
02:03:32.638 --> 02:03:34.400
<i>All right. Hold on. I'm
pushin' through her.</i>

2832
02:03:39.741 --> 02:03:40.742
(GRUNTING)

2833
02:03:40.771 --> 02:03:42.005
<i>I'm pushin' through her!</i>

2834
02:03:43.482 --> 02:03:45.775
<i>- What's your depth?
- 775.</i>

2835
02:03:45.803 --> 02:03:46.735
<i>780.</i>

2836
02:03:46.736 --> 02:03:48.396
<i>Take it up, baby! Ram it home!</i>

2837
02:03:49.613 --> 02:03:51.573
(GRUNTS) <i>Drive on down, A.J.!</i>

2838
02:03:51.574 --> 02:03:53.558
<i>785. Come on.</i>

2839
02:03:54.243 --> 02:03:56.494
<i>- Come on, A.J.!
- Punch it!</i>

2840
02:03:56.495 --> 02:03:57.579
<i>91. Come on.</i>

2841
02:03:57.580 --> 02:03:58.939
<i>792.</i>

2842
02:03:59.572 --> 02:04:00.749
<i>795!</i>

2843
02:04:00.750 --> 02:04:02.080
<i>Drive it down, A.J.!</i>

2844
02:04:03.002 --> 02:04:04.345
<i>797!</i>

2845
02:04:04.799 --> 02:04:06.004
<i>99!</i>

2846
02:04:06.005 --> 02:04:07.825
<i>-  Breakthrough!
- 800!</i>

2847
02:04:07.853 --> 02:04:09.325
<i>802, Harry!</i>

2848
02:04:09.759 --> 02:04:11.551
<i>- Yeah!
- We did it!</i>

2849
02:04:11.552 --> 02:04:12.586
(ALL CHEERING)

2850
02:04:13.387 --> 02:04:15.013
<i>- Yes!
- We did it!</i>

2851
02:04:15.014 --> 02:04:16.227
<i>Yeah!</i>

2852
02:04:16.256 --> 02:04:17.835
<i>Kid, way to go!</i>

2853
02:04:17.864 --> 02:04:19.225
<i>I knew it, baby!</i>

2854
02:04:19.226 --> 02:04:21.311
<i>It's not over till we get
the bomb down that hole.</i>

2855
02:04:21.312 --> 02:04:23.279
<i>Watts, they've got 38 minutes.</i>

2856
02:04:43.918 --> 02:04:45.543
SHARP: <i>Harry, you've
gotta give me that hole.</i>

2857
02:04:45.544 --> 02:04:46.965
<i>I'm gonna need
two more minutes.</i>

2858
02:04:46.994 --> 02:04:48.671
<i>I got a bent pipe
jammed in the hole.</i>

2859
02:04:48.672 --> 02:04:50.976
<i>We gotta cut it out before
we can send that bomb down.</i>

2860
02:04:51.005 --> 02:04:52.125
<i>A.J.!</i>

2861
02:04:52.468 --> 02:04:54.594
CHICK: <i>- She good to go?</i>
A.J.: <i>- Yeah, I'm all set.</i>

2862
02:04:54.595 --> 02:04:55.975
<i>All right.</i>

2863
02:04:56.722 --> 02:04:57.729
(A.J. GRUNTS)

2864
02:05:01.352 --> 02:05:03.603
<i>- All right.
- HARRY: A.J., come on! Make it fast!</i>

2865
02:05:03.604 --> 02:05:05.244
A.J.: <i>I'm goin' as fast as I can!</i>

2866
02:05:05.273 --> 02:05:06.695
<i>There's a lot of gas pressure!</i>

2867
02:05:07.707 --> 02:05:09.033
(EXPLOSIONS)

2868
02:05:13.939 --> 02:05:14.989
<i>You feel that?</i>

2869
02:05:14.990 --> 02:05:17.242
<i>Harry, you gotta give me that hole.
The bomb is almost ready.</i>

2870
02:05:17.243 --> 02:05:19.911
<i>- HARRY: Pull that pipe out!
- Harry, I'm almost through!</i>

2871
02:05:19.912 --> 02:05:21.274
<i>Give me 15 more seconds!</i>

2872
02:05:21.497 --> 02:05:22.602
(RUMBLING)

2873
02:05:27.086 --> 02:05:28.469
<i>Well, this is somethin' new.</i>

2874
02:05:30.798 --> 02:05:31.881
(CRASHING)

2875
02:05:31.882 --> 02:05:33.007
<i>I don't think this thing likes us.</i>

2876
02:05:33.008 --> 02:05:36.136
<i>That's 'cause it knows
we're here to kill it.</i>

2877
02:05:36.137 --> 02:05:37.465
<i>Whoa!</i>

2878
02:05:41.267 --> 02:05:43.628
<i>Hey, what's goin' on up there?</i>

2879
02:05:48.023 --> 02:05:49.696
<i>A.J.!</i>

2880
02:05:50.818 --> 02:05:53.524
<i>- What the hell was that?
- A.J.!</i>

2881
02:05:53.696 --> 02:05:56.106
<i>Goddamn it, I'm finished!</i>

2882
02:05:56.532 --> 02:05:59.451
<i>- A.J., you all right?
- Oh, lot of gas pressure in here, man!</i>

2883
02:05:59.452 --> 02:06:02.203
<i>- Get me out!
- Whoa, whoa, whoa! Hydrogen pocket!</i>

2884
02:06:02.204 --> 02:06:03.219
(SCREAMS)

2885
02:06:11.922 --> 02:06:13.078
(EXCLAIMS)

2886
02:06:16.635 --> 02:06:18.283
- (HARRY GRUNTS)
- (A.J. SCREAMING)

2887
02:06:19.458 --> 02:06:21.313
<i>Oh! Harry!</i>

2888
02:06:21.598 --> 02:06:22.692
<i>Pull me in!</i>

2889
02:06:24.393 --> 02:06:25.394
(GRUNTING)

2890
02:06:25.722 --> 02:06:26.723
(YELLING)

2891
02:06:26.822 --> 02:06:28.369
<i>A.J., hang on!</i>

2892
02:06:28.689 --> 02:06:29.939
(GRUNTING CONTINUES)

2893
02:06:34.195 --> 02:06:35.445
<i>Secure the bomb!</i>

2894
02:06:37.072 --> 02:06:38.249
<i>Sharp, heads up!</i>

2895
02:06:39.700 --> 02:06:40.718
<i>Gruber!</i>

2896
02:06:40.812 --> 02:06:42.109
<i>Get outta there now!</i>

2897
02:06:42.745 --> 02:06:43.752
(ASTEROIDS SHRIEKING)

2898
02:06:43.787 --> 02:06:44.791
<i>Oh, no!</i>

2899
02:06:45.732 --> 02:06:46.854
(EXPLODING)

2900
02:06:51.837 --> 02:06:52.852
(BEAR WHIMPERS)

2901
02:06:53.088 --> 02:06:54.516
<i>Oh, God, no!</i>

2902
02:06:55.674 --> 02:06:56.845
(ALL SCREAMING)

2903
02:07:01.597 --> 02:07:02.682
<i>Look out!</i>

2904
02:07:06.143 --> 02:07:07.541
<i>Help!</i>

2905
02:07:07.955 --> 02:07:09.322
<i>Oh, no!</i>

2906
02:07:11.095 --> 02:07:12.533
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

2907
02:07:15.277 --> 02:07:16.378
(PANTING HEAVILY)

2908
02:07:16.570 --> 02:07:18.071
Do you believe that just happened?

2909
02:07:18.813 --> 02:07:19.831
(GAS HISSING)

2910
02:07:22.201 --> 02:07:24.410
<i>- Sharp, you all right?
- I'm okay.</i>

2911
02:07:24.411 --> 02:07:26.955
<i>- Bear?
- Yeah. I'm here, Harry.</i>

2912
02:07:26.956 --> 02:07:29.541
<i>- A.J.?
- Yeah, I'm okay.</i>

2913
02:07:29.799 --> 02:07:30.807
(GAS HISSING)

2914
02:07:32.086 --> 02:07:33.167
A.J.: <i>We lost Gruber.</i>

2915
02:07:35.273 --> 02:07:36.276
<i>Gruber's dead.</i>

2916
02:07:37.550 --> 02:07:39.706
<i>Let's get that bomb ready and go home.</i>

2917
02:07:47.309 --> 02:07:48.476
SHARP: <i>Oh, my God.</i>

2918
02:07:48.477 --> 02:07:49.484
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

2919
02:07:50.187 --> 02:07:51.577
<i>Is there a problem, Colonel?</i>

2920
02:07:52.147 --> 02:07:54.280
<i>The timer, the remote,
the whole thing's dead.</i>

2921
02:07:54.817 --> 02:07:56.241
<i>What, the bomb is dead?</i>

2922
02:07:56.986 --> 02:07:58.403
<i>No, the trigger's dead.</i>

2923
02:07:58.404 --> 02:08:00.835
<i>It must've gotten damaged
during the rock storm.</i>

2924
02:08:02.992 --> 02:08:04.468
<i>So how do we detonate it?</i>

2925
02:08:09.463 --> 02:08:10.714
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

2926
02:08:14.795 --> 02:08:16.905
TRUMAN: We have 18
minutes to zero barrier.

2927
02:08:17.763 --> 02:08:19.232
We got some bad news.

2928
02:08:19.800 --> 02:08:21.493
The remote
detonator on the bomb

2929
02:08:21.521 --> 02:08:22.831
has been damaged.

2930
02:08:23.679 --> 02:08:25.925
That means that somebody's
gonna have to stay behind.

2931
02:08:28.594 --> 02:08:30.323
SHARP: It takes two
people to fly this thing.

2932
02:08:31.228 --> 02:08:32.713
Either we all stay and die,

2933
02:08:33.532 --> 02:08:35.087
or you guys draw straws.

2934
02:08:35.899 --> 02:08:37.509
I say we all stay and die.

2935
02:08:38.603 --> 02:08:39.720
But that's me.

2936
02:08:40.779 --> 02:08:41.779
I'll draw.

2937
02:08:42.958 --> 02:08:44.005
Let's draw.

2938
02:08:44.992 --> 02:08:46.593
Nobody's gonna draw straws.

2939
02:08:47.995 --> 02:08:49.370
I'll stay and take care of it.

2940
02:08:49.371 --> 02:08:51.497
- Well, I can't live with that sort of thing.
- Nobody asked you

2941
02:08:51.498 --> 02:08:52.790
- if you could live with it, all right?
- LEV: <i>Bullshit!</i>

2942
02:08:52.791 --> 02:08:55.460
No way I will let
you volunteer for this

2943
02:08:55.461 --> 02:08:57.738
so I can go back
to my home country

2944
02:08:57.766 --> 02:08:59.422
like the man who didn't volunteer.

2945
02:08:59.423 --> 02:09:01.132
No way!

2946
02:09:01.133 --> 02:09:03.658
Hey, man, let's
draw, and let's see

2947
02:09:03.687 --> 02:09:05.678
who's gonna stay
up here and dance.

2948
02:09:05.679 --> 02:09:08.514
Guys, I... I know you guys
think I'm crazy right now,

2949
02:09:08.515 --> 02:09:11.250
but I would really
like this responsibility.

2950
02:09:12.311 --> 02:09:15.563
- All right. All right.
- I can do it.

2951
02:09:15.564 --> 02:09:17.482
Let's just draw straws
and get it over with. Come on.

2952
02:09:17.483 --> 02:09:19.233
I ain't drawin' against you, Harry.

2953
02:09:19.234 --> 02:09:20.777
Well, I'm gonna draw
against you, Chick,

2954
02:09:20.778 --> 02:09:22.363
so you better just
go ahead and do it.

2955
02:09:24.156 --> 02:09:26.320
Just gimme this thing.

2956
02:09:33.666 --> 02:09:35.650
Is this good or bad?

2957
02:09:36.108 --> 02:09:37.517
(ADVENTUROUS MUSIC PLAYING)

2958
02:09:41.936 --> 02:09:42.939
Oh, man.

2959
02:09:44.468 --> 02:09:45.470
A.J.: Well.

2960
02:09:46.056 --> 02:09:47.283
We all gotta die, right?

2961
02:09:50.599 --> 02:09:52.520
I'm the guy who gets
to do it saving the world.

2962
02:09:53.644 --> 02:09:55.190
So, uh, let's go.

2963
02:09:55.219 --> 02:09:56.886
We... We got about ten minutes, right?

2964
02:09:59.108 --> 02:10:00.644
You plug this into the port.

2965
02:10:01.318 --> 02:10:02.677
Lift, press...

2966
02:10:03.144 --> 02:10:05.571
hold. That's it.

2967
02:10:05.572 --> 02:10:07.275
Lift, press, hold.
Shouldn't be too tough.

2968
02:10:08.404 --> 02:10:09.587
Even I can't screw this up.

2969
02:10:10.202 --> 02:10:11.251
I'll take him down.

2970
02:10:20.090 --> 02:10:21.157
(HATCH DOOR CLOSES)

2971
02:10:47.406 --> 02:10:49.038
<i>Do me a favor, will ya?</i>

2972
02:10:49.299 --> 02:10:50.624
<i>Just tell Grace that, uh...</i>

2973
02:10:52.638 --> 02:10:54.648
<i>That I'll always be with her, okay?</i>

2974
02:10:57.332 --> 02:10:58.343
<i>Can you do that?</i>

2975
02:11:00.968 --> 02:11:02.984
<i>Yeah. Okay, kid.</i>

2976
02:11:04.973 --> 02:11:06.093
(STEAM HISSING)

2977
02:11:07.425 --> 02:11:08.413
Aah!

2978
02:11:09.913 --> 02:11:11.015
<i>Give this to Truman.</i>

2979
02:11:11.680 --> 02:11:13.344
<i>Make sure Truman gets that.</i>

2980
02:11:13.780 --> 02:11:14.789
<i>Get in there!</i>

2981
02:11:20.814 --> 02:11:22.565
<i>It's my turn now.</i>

2982
02:11:22.566 --> 02:11:23.691
(GASPING)

2983
02:11:23.899 --> 02:11:25.847
Harry! Harry!

2984
02:11:26.320 --> 02:11:27.921
You can't do this to me!

2985
02:11:29.673 --> 02:11:30.984
It's my job!

2986
02:11:31.960 --> 02:11:33.811
<i>You go take care
of my little girl now.</i>

2987
02:11:34.949 --> 02:11:36.070
<i>That's your job.</i>

2988
02:11:39.416 --> 02:11:41.124
<i>Always thought
of you as a son.</i>

2989
02:11:41.607 --> 02:11:42.726
<i>Always.</i>

2990
02:11:43.913 --> 02:11:46.296
<i>But I'd be damn proud
to have you marry Grace.</i>

2991
02:11:48.050 --> 02:11:49.073
(CRYING) Harry.

2992
02:11:49.971 --> 02:11:50.995
<i>You take care of yourself.</i>

2993
02:11:51.470 --> 02:11:52.845
- Harry, no!
<i>- I love you, pal.</i>

2994
02:11:52.846 --> 02:11:54.707
Harry, I love you!

2995
02:11:54.736 --> 02:11:56.224
Don't, Harry!
Wait a minute!

2996
02:11:56.225 --> 02:11:58.643
<i>- My son.</i>
- Don't do this, Harry!

2997
02:11:58.644 --> 02:12:01.201
<i>Don't do this! Harry!</i>

2998
02:12:03.924 --> 02:12:05.033
(HATCH DOOR CLOSING)

2999
02:12:09.822 --> 02:12:10.854
What happened?

3000
02:12:11.990 --> 02:12:14.275
That crazy, stubborn son of a...

3001
02:12:16.750 --> 02:12:17.752
(GRUNTS)

3002
02:12:21.250 --> 02:12:22.986
<i>Well, this was a real good idea.</i>

3003
02:12:24.545 --> 02:12:27.482
<i>All right, let's go, Sharp.
Let's get our team outta here.</i>

3004
02:12:33.387 --> 02:12:35.746
Come on! Let's get
ready to initiate thrusters!

3005
02:12:36.341 --> 02:12:37.974
Strap in, guys! Let's go!

3006
02:12:37.975 --> 02:12:39.427
Strap it in, guys!

3007
02:12:39.739 --> 02:12:40.810
Get the O2 masks.

3008
02:12:40.811 --> 02:12:42.544
Are they green? Are they green?

3009
02:12:43.438 --> 02:12:45.648
I can't believe this is
going down like this.

3010
02:12:45.649 --> 02:12:46.645
You all right?

3011
02:12:47.150 --> 02:12:49.467
O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.

3012
02:12:49.495 --> 02:12:50.825
Engine board is green.

3013
02:12:53.156 --> 02:12:55.202
WOMAN: (ON PA) <i>T-minus
three minutes and counting.</i>

3014
02:12:55.993 --> 02:12:58.562
HARRY: <i>Houston, do you
copy? This is Harry Stamper.</i>

3015
02:12:59.830 --> 02:13:00.835
It's down there.

3016
02:13:03.625 --> 02:13:05.398
MAN: <i>Electrical systems primed.</i>

3017
02:13:05.427 --> 02:13:07.843
WOMAN: <i>A.P.U. is set. Oxidizers are loading.</i>

3018
02:13:08.589 --> 02:13:11.299
MAN: <i>Houston, we're outta here
in T minus three minutes.</i>

3019
02:13:13.093 --> 02:13:14.116
Daddy!

3020
02:13:14.257 --> 02:13:15.261
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

3021
02:13:15.262 --> 02:13:16.288
Hi, Gracie.

3022
02:13:17.087 --> 02:13:18.100
Hi, honey.

3023
02:13:19.134 --> 02:13:21.436
<i>Grace, I know I promised you
I was comin' home.</i>

3024
02:13:23.812 --> 02:13:25.267
I don't under... Understand.

3025
02:13:26.440 --> 02:13:28.830
(SIGHS) <i>Looks like I'm gonna
have to break that promise.</i>

3026
02:13:32.529 --> 02:13:33.622
I, um...

3027
02:13:34.607 --> 02:13:35.927
I lied to you, too,

3028
02:13:36.650 --> 02:13:39.177
when I told you that
I didn't want to be like you.

3029
02:13:41.413 --> 02:13:42.849
Because I am like you.

3030
02:13:44.264 --> 02:13:46.238
<i>And everything
good that I have</i>

3031
02:13:46.266 --> 02:13:48.239
<i>inside of me, I
have from you.</i>

3032
02:13:49.852 --> 02:13:51.592
<i>I love you so much, Daddy.</i>

3033
02:13:52.489 --> 02:13:53.934
<i>I'm so proud of you.</i>

3034
02:13:54.927 --> 02:13:55.989
<i>I'm so scared.</i>

3035
02:13:57.172 --> 02:13:58.473
(VOICE BREAKING)
<i>I'm so scared.</i>

3036
02:13:59.819 --> 02:14:00.911
I know it, baby.

3037
02:14:02.400 --> 02:14:04.403
But there won't be anything
to be scared of soon.

3038
02:14:07.076 --> 02:14:09.936
<i>Gracie, I want you to know
that A.J. saved us.</i>

3039
02:14:11.385 --> 02:14:12.389
<i>He did.</i>

3040
02:14:14.279 --> 02:14:15.716
<i>I want you to tell Chick</i>

3041
02:14:16.296 --> 02:14:17.904
<i>that I couldn't have
done it without him.</i>

3042
02:14:18.054 --> 02:14:19.138
<i>None of it.</i>

3043
02:14:21.952 --> 02:14:23.466
<i>I want you to take care of A.J.</i>

3044
02:14:24.181 --> 02:14:25.186
(CRYING)

3045
02:14:28.543 --> 02:14:30.933
I wish I could be there
to walk you down the aisle.

3046
02:14:34.800 --> 02:14:35.792
But I'll...

3047
02:14:38.428 --> 02:14:41.209
(SIGHS) I'll look in on you
from time to time, okay, honey?

3048
02:14:44.726 --> 02:14:46.268
I love you, Grace.

3049
02:14:46.269 --> 02:14:48.479
(SOBBING) I love you, too.

3050
02:14:48.480 --> 02:14:49.503
I gotta go now, honey.

3051
02:14:49.636 --> 02:14:50.878
Daddy, no.

3052
02:14:52.160 --> 02:14:54.355
No, no, Dad, no.

3053
02:14:56.727 --> 02:14:58.089
(MAN ON RADIO, MUFFLED)

3054
02:15:01.576 --> 02:15:03.107
WATTS: O.M.S. pod pre-start.

3055
02:15:03.136 --> 02:15:04.997
O2 vents locked, pressure loaded.

3056
02:15:07.082 --> 02:15:09.583
<i>What the hell's goin' on up there?
Why haven't you guys left yet?</i>

3057
02:15:09.584 --> 02:15:12.086
We're going, Harry. Houston.

3058
02:15:12.087 --> 02:15:14.805
- We got O.M.S. pod pre-start.
- Pod pre-start confirmed.

3059
02:15:16.717 --> 02:15:17.834
(ENGINE CHOKING)

3060
02:15:18.510 --> 02:15:19.635
- What's the problem?
- I don't know.

3061
02:15:19.636 --> 02:15:21.260
- What's wrong?
- Fix it now!

3062
02:15:23.056 --> 02:15:25.266
No time, no time!

3063
02:15:25.267 --> 02:15:27.579
- What?
- What's that?

3064
02:15:31.106 --> 02:15:33.441
- Where you goin'?
- Come on. We're stayin', we're goin'.

3065
02:15:33.442 --> 02:15:35.443
We're stayin', we're goin'.
Make up your mind.

3066
02:15:35.444 --> 02:15:37.139
<i>Sharp, get out of here now.</i>

3067
02:15:37.168 --> 02:15:38.365
<i>You got less than three minutes.</i>

3068
02:15:42.659 --> 02:15:44.243
Come on, Watts. Come on, come on.

3069
02:15:44.244 --> 02:15:46.115
Blow the bomb, Harry. We're with you.

3070
02:15:46.538 --> 02:15:48.186
Uh, it's stuck. Yes?

3071
02:15:48.214 --> 02:15:49.858
Back off! You don't
know the components!

3072
02:15:50.292 --> 02:15:52.458
<i>Components, American
components,</i>

3073
02:15:52.486 --> 02:15:53.878
<i>Russian components.</i>

3074
02:15:53.879 --> 02:15:55.428
All made in Taiwan!

3075
02:15:55.943 --> 02:15:57.647
We're gettin' tight for ignition, Freedom.

3076
02:16:00.927 --> 02:16:02.386
Houston, we've got no fire.

3077
02:16:02.387 --> 02:16:04.555
- What does that mean?
- It means we got a busted ship.

3078
02:16:04.556 --> 02:16:07.224
A busted ship?
And I'm strapped in here.

3079
02:16:07.225 --> 02:16:09.488
I had a great spot picked out there.

3080
02:16:09.519 --> 02:16:10.728
CAPCOM: Freedom,
you fire that engine.

3081
02:16:10.729 --> 02:16:12.897
If there's not a way, you find a way.
The clock's tickin'.

3082
02:16:12.898 --> 02:16:15.225
Let's go!
Let's fire that engine, Freedom!

3083
02:16:15.484 --> 02:16:16.640
<i>You got less than a minute.</i>

3084
02:16:16.669 --> 02:16:18.132
<i>Don't think I won't blow this thing.</i>

3085
02:16:20.572 --> 02:16:21.798
<i>Sharp, get out of here.</i>

3086
02:16:21.827 --> 02:16:23.157
<i>It's gettin' bad down here.</i>

3087
02:16:23.158 --> 02:16:25.326
I know how to fix it. Please, move.

3088
02:16:25.327 --> 02:16:27.745
I have to take you away
if you don't move.

3089
02:16:27.746 --> 02:16:29.636
Watts, you gotta get that shuttle started.

3090
02:16:29.665 --> 02:16:30.802
You gotta fire it up now!

3091
02:16:30.832 --> 02:16:32.875
<i>Damn it, Sharp!
Get off this rock!</i>

3092
02:16:32.876 --> 02:16:35.044
I'm telling you, please, move!

3093
02:16:35.045 --> 02:16:36.943
This is how we fix problem

3094
02:16:37.287 --> 02:16:39.591
in the Russian space station!

3095
02:16:40.342 --> 02:16:42.240
Because I don't want
to stay here

3096
02:16:42.268 --> 02:16:43.511
anymore!

3097
02:16:43.817 --> 02:16:44.822
(WHIRRING)

3098
02:16:45.263 --> 02:16:47.230
Yeah! Finally!

3099
02:16:48.106 --> 02:16:49.225
We can go home!

3100
02:16:49.226 --> 02:16:50.581
She's coming back.
She's coming back.

3101
02:16:50.638 --> 02:16:51.644
We're hot!

3102
02:16:51.645 --> 02:16:53.066
Watts! Let's go, let's go!

3103
02:16:54.708 --> 02:16:56.793
Rain all you want, you son of a bitch.

3104
02:16:58.068 --> 02:17:00.918
Let's go! We don't have time!
Hurry, hurry. We got no time!

3105
02:17:01.196 --> 02:17:03.239
Initiate thrusters on my mark!

3106
02:17:03.240 --> 02:17:05.160
Two, one, mark!

3107
02:17:05.250 --> 02:17:06.445
(THRUSTERS FIRING)

3108
02:17:13.166 --> 02:17:15.776
Come on. Get some altitude.
Let's go, let's go.

3109
02:17:15.877 --> 02:17:17.166
(ALL YELLING)

3110
02:17:18.338 --> 02:17:19.642
Freedom has max thrust!

3111
02:17:27.222 --> 02:17:28.244
Thank you, Harry.

3112
02:17:30.131 --> 02:17:31.447
(CRUMPLING EXPLOSIONS)

3113
02:17:35.897 --> 02:17:36.998
(HARRY SCREAMING)

3114
02:17:40.026 --> 02:17:41.902
Shuttle's out of range.
Still no detonation.

3115
02:17:41.903 --> 02:17:43.010
(GRUNTING)

3116
02:17:46.658 --> 02:17:47.907
Something's not right.

3117
02:17:47.935 --> 02:17:49.048
Too much time has gone by.

3118
02:17:51.246 --> 02:17:52.660
Zero barrier's about to
be breached.

3119
02:17:52.689 --> 02:17:53.581
One minute.

3120
02:17:53.582 --> 02:17:56.417
Harry, come on. Press that button.

3121
02:17:56.418 --> 02:17:58.066
We're goin' back and do it ourselves.

3122
02:17:58.095 --> 02:17:59.816
Just don't. Wait one minute.

3123
02:18:00.659 --> 02:18:01.722
(GRUNTING)

3124
02:18:04.843 --> 02:18:06.510
Dan, we're about to cross the threshold.

3125
02:18:06.511 --> 02:18:07.887
Come on. Press the button.

3126
02:18:07.888 --> 02:18:09.903
Colonel, I'm askin' you!

3127
02:18:10.672 --> 02:18:12.786
<i>Just one more minute!</i>

3128
02:18:15.812 --> 02:18:16.817
(GRUNTS)

3129
02:18:19.555 --> 02:18:20.895
Press the button, Stamper.

3130
02:18:24.534 --> 02:18:25.536
Come on.

3131
02:18:28.648 --> 02:18:30.044
Harry'll do it. I know it.

3132
02:18:32.287 --> 02:18:33.614
He doesn't know how to fail.

3133
02:18:41.671 --> 02:18:43.046
We win, Gracie!

3134
02:18:44.507 --> 02:18:45.514
Press it!

3135
02:18:45.543 --> 02:18:46.644
(BEEPING RAPIDLY)

3136
02:18:46.673 --> 02:18:47.677
(EXHALES)

3137
02:18:48.829 --> 02:18:50.119
(THRILLING MUSIC PLAYING)

3138
02:18:51.263 --> 02:18:52.323
(CAMERA CLICKING)

3139
02:18:55.734 --> 02:18:56.870
(EXPLODING)

3140
02:18:59.053 --> 02:19:00.651
(CRUMPLING EXPLOSIONS)

3141
02:19:07.348 --> 02:19:08.360
(GRUNTS)

3142
02:19:09.536 --> 02:19:11.013
(EXPLODING CONTINUES)

3143
02:19:16.735 --> 02:19:17.739
(SCREAMING)

3144
02:19:18.833 --> 02:19:21.356
MAN: (ON PA) <i>We have
detonation. Confirming detonation.</i>

3145
02:19:31.977 --> 02:19:33.395
(RUMBLING)

3146
02:19:39.437 --> 02:19:41.855
MAN: <i>The two halves are
gonna miss us by 400 miles,</i>

3147
02:19:41.856 --> 02:19:44.098
<i>and most of the small particles
have been vaporized.</i>

3148
02:19:44.454 --> 02:19:45.867
(CROWD CHEERING WILDLY)

3149
02:19:56.204 --> 02:19:59.039
- Houston, we're comin' home.
- We copy that, Freedom.

3150
02:19:59.040 --> 02:20:00.063
Yo, Harry.

3151
02:20:01.084 --> 02:20:02.086
You the man.

3152
02:20:03.067 --> 02:20:04.352
(SWEEPING MUSIC PLAYING)

3153
02:20:04.934 --> 02:20:06.324
(CONTINUES CHEERING)

3154
02:20:27.632 --> 02:20:28.838
(TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING)

3155
02:20:55.680 --> 02:20:57.320
Kennedy, we see you.

3156
02:20:57.726 --> 02:20:59.070
And you never looked so good.

3157
02:20:59.601 --> 02:21:01.272
